Commentary.Commentary: Before that, the man who got a 4-fer, is caught for a quick chat. He says that it was a good day for them. Tells that in the first session, there was some moisture on the pitch and they wanted to bowl on good line and length. Tells that Ashwin has been bowling superbly. Praises Siraj and says that he is really happy for him.

Right! The Indian bowlers have done their job. It is up to their batters now. The Australian batters? Well, Paine would've surely wanted a lot more from his batters after winning the toss. The first thing the Indian openers would look to do is negotiate and go unscathed to Stumps on Day 1. Will they be able to do so? The Australian bowlers will look to strike early once the Indians come out to bat. Who will partner Agarwal? Will the debutant Gill will be asked to come out to bat and negate the nervy few overs? It is going to be an interesting few overs which will come your way shortly.

The Indian bowlers were superb throughout the day, led by skipper Rahane who made a few interesting bowling changes as well as field placements. It was Bumrah who gave them the breakthrough and Ashwin got two in the first session. When the Aussies stitched a stand, Bumrah returned to remove Head and put India on top again with Siraj getting his first Test wicket as he got better of well-settled Labuschagne. Bumrah and Siraj then removed the tail. Bumrah ended up with 4 while Ashwin got 3. Siraj, on debut, got two wickets while Jadeja got the wicket of the last man.

Earlier in the day, Paine won the toss and opted to bat first. The decision didn't pay off as the Aussies lost Burns early. Wade too fell after playing a few good shots. However, Labuschagne and Head weathered the storm and added 87 to pull things back. But both departed in quick succession to leave Australia reeling at 134/5. Paine and Green negotiated till Tea but once they returned, they followed each other back in the pavilion. Paine failed to repeat the rescue act and fell cheaply and the Aussies eventually bundled out for a low total.

What a sensational bowling performance from India! Led by Bumrah and equally helped by Ashwin's spin, India have rolled over Australia for a paltry score. Apart form Head and Labuschagne, and to some extent Wade, none of the Aussie batters offered any resistance. And the mentioned batters failed to continue and now Australia are in a big trouble.

OUT! CAUGHT! Jadeja gets the last man. A fine catch from Siraj. A floated ball around middle, Cummins looks for the slog but ends up getting a top edge. The ball goes high in the air towards long on. Sirak settles underneath and takes the catch easily. Australia have been bowled out for 195.

Floated around off, pushed towards the cover fielder.

FOUR! Hazlewood is off the mark with a boundary. Bumrah looks for a yorker but ends up bowling it down the leg side. Hazlewood tickles it down to the fine leg fence for a boundary. End of an eventful over.
Josh Hazlewood is the last man in. Can Bumrah remove him first ball?

OUT! No willow there and it is Umpire's Call on Wickets Hitting So, he has to go. 9 down and Bumrah has 4. After getting hit for a six and a boundary on back of a length ball, Bumrah lands this one on a good length and makes it to come back in as Lyon looks for a drive but misses to get hit on the pad.

Australians, on the other hand, would hope to see these two add a few more valuable runs. If the Indians get the two wickets, they will have to face a few tricky overs from the Aussie pacers. So, an interesting final phase of play awaits.

NOT OUT! And a loud cheer from the crowd as they see the decision flashing on the big screen. That looked a tough call and the umpire believes that the bat has crossed the line when Pant took the bails off. Maybe they have given the benefit of doubt to the batter. Coming to the delivery, it was fuller and around off, Green pushes it towards cover. They go for the single but stop in the middle and then go for it again as the cover fielder throws the ball at the striker's end. Pant takes the bails off. The Indians are not sure as one of them is heard saying he is in on the stumps mic. Replays roll in and the third umpire takes his own time to confirm the decision. A tough call but not out is the decision which the TV umpire comes up with. Rahane is not happy as he is having a word with the umpire. Paine survives a nervy moment.

Run out appeal taken upstairs! The Indians are not too sure. Let's see what the replays show. That looks really, really close. The bat is on the line it seems. We are back for the final session of Day 1. Tim Paine and Cameron Green are the two Aussie batters. The Indian players make their way out in the middle. Ashwin to start after Tea. Here we go..
... Day 1, Session 3...

An intriguing session of the play comes to an end! It was Australia who looked on top after the end of the first hour as Labuschagne along with Head added runs a bit quickly and without facing many challenges. However, Bumrah returned to remove Head while Labuschagne became the victim of debutant Siraj just 2 away from his half ton. With 5 down for 136, the Aussies are looking in a spot of bother. The good thing for them though is that skipper Paine who did the rescue act in the last game is out in the middle and a lot will depend on him, as far as Australia are concerned. The Indians will return for the final session of the day with an aim to get rid of Paine as quickly as possible and then try to get the other wickets. Join us for the final session in a short while.

The replays show that the ball would've just clipped the leg stump. So, the onfield decision stays but India doesn't lose their review.

DRS TIME! With just 1 second left on the timer, Rahane has asked for the review. Looked to be going down the leg side. Let's see what the replays have got to show. Clear gap between bat and ball. Just wide! A maiden to begin from Ashwin. Flatter and around middle, bounces extra as Labuschagne fends it wide of the man at short leg.
On middle, blocked by Labuschagne.
Full and on middle, worked towards square leg. They think for the run but opt against it.
Floated on off, blocked off the front foot.
Flatter and around middle, clipped towards mid-wicket.
Flatter and around middle, worked towards short leg.
Who will begin the second session from the other end? Will it be spin from the other end? Yes. Ravichandran Ashwin it is.
On the pads, clipped to fine leg for one. 2 off Siraj's first over in Tests.
Good length and around off, Head dabs it towards cover and they take a quick run.
In the channel outside off, Head lets it be.
Back of a length and just outside off, poked towards the point fielder.
Shortish and around off, Head keeps it out.
Siraj is right on the money! A length delivery around off, Head blocks off his back foot.

We are back for the second session! The Indian players have taken to the field already. Marnus Labuschagne and Travis Head have made their way out to the middle as well. Who will take the ball for India post the Lunch break? Yes! Finally the debutant gets to bowl. After 27 overs in the game, Mohammed Siraj gets his chance now. What a proud moment for him nonetheless.
... Day 1, Session 2 ...

The Indian bowlers were on the money straight away! Bumrah and Umesh kept things tight a the start. Bumrah drew the first blood as he removed Burns. To everyone's surprise, Rahane tossed the ball to Ashwin. And the off-spinner didn't disappoint as he got a couple of wickets. He has looked in a terrific rhythm and the way the pitch is behaving, it is not going to be easy for the Aussie batters once they return for the second session. We will be back for the second session soon.

Earlier in the game, Australia won the toss and opted to bowl first. Burns failed to open his account. Wade looked good as he played a few classy drives but lost his wicket as he tried to take on Ashwin. Smith failed once again as he became Ashwin's 2nd victim and fell for a duck. Labuschagne along with Head are battling out in the middle. The duo have added 27 between them but it hasn't been easy for them out in the middle. Head has scored just 4 off 37 balls while Labuschagne has survived a few close chances.

A terrific session of play for the visitors! It was Bumrah who struck early and then twin wickets from Ashwin have put India in a good position at the end of the first session. They have bowled superbly so far. Interestingly, debutant Siraj didn't get the chance to have a go with the ball as yet!
Quicker one on the pads, flicked towards the leg side. With that, it is Lunch on Day 1.
Floated on middle, blocked off the front foot.

NOT OUT! It is missing the stumps. It never looked that it would be going over the timbers but that is the case and Labuschagne survives. Good use of the technology from him. A tossed up delivery around middle, he goes for the sweep but he misses to get hit on the pad. The Indians appeal and the finger goes up. Marnus calls for the review straightaway. Replays roll now. Hot Spot and RTS show no bat. But to everyone's surprise, the ball is going over the stumps. The extra bounce which Ashwin is generating takes it over the stumps. Good call to review from Labuschagne.

Labuschagne is given out LBW but he goes for the review quickly. Is there any bat? Let's see if Hot Spot detects anything. Nothing on it and nothing on RTS either. That should be plumb then. Hang on! It is missing the stumps. Labuschagne survives.
Labuschagne is taking his time! He wants to make sure that this is the last over before Lunch.
Shortish and around middle, worked towards mid on for a single.
Full and on middle, pushed to the left of Ashwin for nothing.
Flatter and around off, worked towards the leg side.
Tossed up and just outside off, turns away a touch as Labuschagne lets it go to the keeper.
Down the leg side, turns further down as Pant fails to collect it down the leg side. The ball races to the fine leg fence but Mayank does well to get to the ball and pull it back in.
Tossed up and outside off, driven towards cover for a quick single.
Flat and around off, blocked out.
In the air... safe! Jadeja bowls this one full and bowls it wide. Labuschagne reaches out and looks to drive but gets a top edge. The ball lands safely outside the ring at cover. Two taken.
FOUR! Jadeja giving away easy runs here. Short and wide outside off, Labuschagne slams it through point and bags another boundary.
Maiden from Ashwin. Flatter and around off, Head keeps it out.
On off, a solid front foot block from Head this time.
Flatter and around off, worked towards mid-wicket.
Quicker one outside off, Head lets it be.
Full and around off, watchfully blocked.
Floated on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
On middle, defended.
Fuller and around off, Labuschagne comes forward and defends. Pant encourages Jadeja from behind, telling him to keep bowling the same length.
Flatter and around off, blocked.
Full and on middle, Labuschagne flicks but can't beat the man at mid-wicket who makes a diving stop to his right.
FOUR! Nicely done! Short and wide outside off, Labuschagne stays back and then just forces it gently wide of the short third man fielder. It races away to the fence.
Short and wide outside off, pushed towards point.
Floated around middle, Head defends it out.
Fuller and around off, pushed back to Ashwin.
Full and on middle, Labuschagne flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single. The single brings up 50 for Australia.
Down the leg side, flicked wide of the man at square leg for a run.
Tossed up on middle, Head stays back and blocks.
Floated on middle, played back to Ashwin by Head.
A maiden from Jadeja. Full and around middle, pushed towards mid on.
This time Labuschagne gets behind the line to defend off his front foot.
Beaten this time! Jadeja fires this one just outside off, it pitches and then turns away a touch. Good take from Pant.
Flatter and around off, Labuschagne does well to block off his back foot.
Floated around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and wide, driven hard but straight to Gill at short cover.
Around off and middle, Head stays back to keep it out.
Fuller and around off, flicked to deep mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Crunched! Short and wide outside off, Labuschagne rocks back and slams it wide of Jadeja this time. He gives it a chase but fails to stop.
Short and just outside off, Labuschagne punches but finds the cover fielder.
Flatter and around middle, blocked.
Play and a miss! A flatter ball just outside off, Labuschagne looks to punch it off the back foot but it bounces extra and Labuschagne fails to connect.
Flatter and around off, worked wide of the man at mid on for a run. Decent start from Jadeja.
On middle, pushed to mid on for a quick single.
Floats this one down the leg side. Head looks to flick but misses.
Flatter and just outside off, punched towards the off side.
Full again, pushed towards mid off.
Fuller and around off to begin, pushed off the front foot towards point.
Bowling change! No Mohammed Siraj yet. Here's Ravindra Jadeja with the ball.
Single to end another superb over from Ashwin. Full and wide, Head goes for the drive and connects it well. It is to the right side of Jadeja who makes a diving stop but they take the single.
Fuller and around middle, blocked.
On off, this time Head comes forward and keeps it out.
Flatter and around middle, clipped towards mid-wicket.

What happened there? Floated around off, Head looks to work it on the leg side but it spins away to beat the bat. The ball hits his pad and then lobs towards silly point. The fielder takes the catch and they appeal but not out says the umpire. The Indians think for the review but in the end opt against it.
Loopy ball outside off, Head drives it hard but it hits Vihari at silly point.
A length ball outside off, defended on the leg side.
A fuller ball on the stumps, Marnus misses and gets hit on the pads. Inside edge there seem to save him from getting trapped right in front.
A good length ball around off, defended solidly on the front foot by Marnus.
Length ball outside off, Marnus leaves it alone.
A fuller length ball, Marnus watches and plays it towards point.
Length ball just outside off, Marnus defends it solidly.
Dot to end! Flatter and around off, Head goes back and pushes it towards cover.
Full and on middle, forced towards mid on.
On off, kept out.
On the pads, worked towards the square leg fielder. It went uppishly but was wide of the man at short leg.
Flatter and just outside off, forced to deep cover for a run.
Flatter and just around off, punched towards cover.
Beaten! Superb delivery from Bumrah. Just around off on a good length. Head has to play at it. He does so but is beaten all ends up. Terrific from Bumrah.
A length ball outside off, Head blocks this one out.
Fuller ball on the stumps, Head flick this one to mid on
Length ball outside off, nudged it soflty towards mid on and Marnus takes a quick single.

NOT OUT! It is going over the stumps. Extra bounce saves Head. A length ball outside off, Labuschagne looks to defend but this one comes back in nicely and beats the inside edge. The ball hits the pad and the Indians appeal but nothing from the umpire. Indians take it upstairs. Replays roll in and they show that the ball would go over the timbers. India lose their review.

Review time! Indians have taken the appeal against Labuschagne. It is for LBW. Let's see what the third umpire has to say. It is a fair delivery. Nothing on the Hot spot and nothing on the RTS either. Time for the Ball Tracker. Missing! It is going over the stumps. So, India lose one of their reviews.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Flatter and around middle, Head goes back to block it out.
On off, kept out.
Full and around off, driven towards mid off.
Who's in next? Travis Head it is at number 5. Aggressive field set for him here. Two slips, one short leg and one at silly point.

OUT! TAKEN DOWN THE LEG SIDE! Ashwin removes the big fish. Smith falls for a duck. Lovely from Ashwin. Bowls a loopy ball around middle and leg, Smith lunges forward to work it on the leg side but ends up hitting it straight to the leg slip fielder. Pujara there takes a good catch. Ashwin removes Smith again. Terrific stuff from the Indians here.

Turn and bounce! Tossed up around middle, it pitches and then boucnes an turns sharply as Smith is beaten. Pant fails to collecy to his left as well and they run two byes as the ball goes towards fine leg.
Quick single! Flatter and around middle, Labuschagne goes back and pushes it towards mid off. They go for a single.
Maiden over first up to Smith. A length ball outside off, blocked by Smith towards mid on.
A length ball just outside off, left alone by Smith.
A fuller length ball outside off, Smith plays it towards mid on.
Length ball outside off, Smith bunts this out.
Good length ball outside off, Smith shuffles and plays it towards mid on.
Fuller length ball on the stumps, defended straight back.
A mild appeal! A tossed up ball around the pad, Labuschagne lets it be and is hit on the pad. An enquiry but turned down. End of a successful over from Ashwin.
Smith is in.
Steven Smith comes to bat

DRINKS! It looked like Australia will end the first hour on top with Wade looking solid but he decided to take on the spinner and has fell against the run of play. So, India will be the happier side between the two.

OUT! CAUGHT! Jadeja holds on! There was some confusion but he did really well to keep his eyes on the ball to hold onto it. A poor shot from Wade. He was playing aggressively and he once again tried to go after Ashwin. A Tossed up ball around off and middle, Wade dances down the track and looks to hammer it on the leg side but ends up getting a top edge. The ball goes high in the air towards mid-wicket. Jadeja and Gill go for the catch but Jadeja calls for it but Gill doesn't see that. They both go for it and almost collides with each other. However, Jadeja keeps his eyes on the ball to take a fine catch.
FOUR! Nicely done! Full and on middle and leg, Wade gets in position and nicely paddles it through short fine leg for a boundary. Wade moves to 30 off just 38 balls.
Floated around off, blocked off the front foot.
Full and outside off, Wade goes for the sweep but misses. It bounces extra as Pant fails to catch it as it hits him near his chest.
Shortish and just outsude off, punched towards cover for a single.
Fuller ball on the pads, flicked away towards fine leg for a single.
A length ball outside off, defended straight back.
Another one that jags back in. A length ball outside off, comes back sharply to hit Marnus on the pads. He thought this one will move away but it came back in but hit him high on the pad.
A fuller length ball on middle, flicked to mid on.
Outside off, Labuschagne lets it be.
Driven nicely! Full and wide, Wade drives it to the right side of the man at mid off. The fielder gives it a chase but Wade gets three more.
Dot to end! Good first over from Ashwin. Fuller and around middle, Labuschagne flicks but the short leg fielder stops.
Quicker one just outside off, Labuschagne goes on the back foot and looks to cut but misses.
Just wide! Good stuff from Ashwin. Flat and around off, turns in and bounces extra. It lobs wide of the leg slip. Replays show there was some bat. Labuschagne is a lucky man.
Flatter and outside off, tucked towards square leg.
Fuller and around off and middle, swept to deep square leg for a single.
Flatter and around off to begin, pushed back to the bowler.
First change! Time for some spin. Here's Ravichandran Ashwin with the ball.
Good ball to end the over. A length ball around off, jags back in to hit Marnus on the pads.
Close to the off stump on a length, but still left alone by Marnus.
Length ball outside off, pushed towards point.
Good length ball outside off, Marnus leaves it alone.
Fuller length outside off, Wade drives this one through covers to collect three more runs.
Good fuller length ball outside off, Wade leaves it alone.
Wide outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms.
Goes for the bouncer but this one doesn't rise much. Labuschagne pulls it wide of the fine leg fielder for a brace.
Another good length delivery around off, blocked off the back foot.
Around off on a good length, blocked.
Fuller and outside off, driven well but straight to the cover fielder.
4 Slips in place at the moment. Seeing Bumrah shaping the ball away, Rahane has given that extra man for him in the cordon.
Back of a length and around off, pushed towards mid on.
Outside off, left alone.
Excellent stuff from Umesh in this over. Pitches this one around off and middle and it is shortish in length. It comes back in as Wade looks to defend. He misses to get hit high on the pad.
A length ball this time and it is outside off. A leave this time from Wade.
Beaten this time! Umesh runs in and bowls it just outside off, Wade this time goes for the big booming drive but a hint of away movement means he makes no connection.
Another fuller one outside off, Wade is not interested again.
Fuller but wide outside off, Wade lets it go to Pant.
Labuschagne makes another leave as Bumrah bowls it outside off on a good length.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Good length and around off, kept out.
Nicely done! Full ball on middle, Wade flicks it through mid-wicket and runs three before Ashwin can return the ball.
This one comes back again as Wade is hit high on the pad.
Good leave! This was just outside off and it came back in nicely as Wade allowed it to go to the keeper. Top stuff from Bumrah here.
On the pads again, Wade nudges it through square leg for a single to keep the strike for the next over.
Down the leg side. Wade lets it be.
Full but wide outside off, left alone by Wade.
Labuschagne is up and running now! Umesh sprays on the pads and he flicks it to fine leg for one.
Taps the next one towards point and gets to the other end. Good stuff from Wade.
FOUR! SHOT! Superb shot! Umesh is looking for some swing and hence he is pitching it up. This one is wide outside off and Wade creams it through the cover region for a boundary.
Fullish and on middle, Labuschagne pushes it towards mid on. End of a successful over for Bumrah.
Little wide outside off, Labuschagne lets it be.

What a ripper! Bumrah is looking superb for the Indians here. Another brilliant delivery from him. It is just outside off on a good length. Maybe a little on the shortish side. Marnus stays back and has a poke off his back foot but is beaten.
Good length and just outside off, blocked.
Marnus Labuschagne comes in to bat at number 3.

OUT! TAKEN! Bumrah draws first blood. Lovely stuff from him. Burns poor run continues as he departs for a duck. Bumrah runs in and bowls a good length ball just outside off, Burns comes on the front foot and looks to defend but ends up getting an outside edge. The ball goes behind and it is a simple chance for Pant. They all go up in appeal and the finger is raised.
Good length and around off, pushed to the left of the bowler.
Length ball around off and middle, Wade keeps it out solidly.
Around off on a length, Wade defends it out.
Shortish and around off, poked towards point.
FOUR! Gorgeous drive! Full and wide outside off, Wade this time drills it through cover-point and it races away to the fence.

Is that a drop? Has Wade got a life here? A lovely ball from Umesh. A length ball around off, Wade is squared up as he looks to defend. The ball goes to the left of debutant Gill at second slip. He dives to that side but it looked like it bounced just before his hands. They take two as the ball goes towards third man. A chance but it was a very difficult one.
Fine shot for nothing. Full and wide outside off, Wade nails the drive but finds Jadeja at covers.

That's an absolute ripper! What a delivery to end the over. A fuller ball just outside off, Burns comes forward and looks to defned as he plays for the swing but it goes straight to beat the outside edge. Another fine over from Bumrah.
Misfield and a run! First run off Bumrah. A length ball around off, Wade pushes it towards the left of Gully. Rahane there misfields and allows a single.
Outside off, left alone.
Nicely bowled! A length ball around middle and off, Wade looks to defend but it comes back in a touch. He misses to get hit high on the pad.
Fuller and around off, Wade keeps it out.
Good length and around off, Wade covers his stumps and lets it go.
Little too wide for the right-hander. Burns lets it go to the keeper. The ball moves late in the air.

Wade and Australia are underway! Full and wide outside off, Wade this time goes for the drive and finds the gap at cover-point. The cover fielder gives it a chase and returns the ball to the keeper but not before the Aussie openers take three.
Outside off, easy leave again.
Another one outside off, Wade is happy leaving it alone this early in his innings.
Full and wide outside off, Wade is not lured into going for the drive way from his body as he shoulders arms.
Yadav runs in and bowls the length ball outside off, Wade covers his stumps and lets it be.
Who will bowl from the other end? Umesh Yadav it is.

Beaten! Good testing first over from Bumrah! After bowling good length deliveries, Bumrah bowls it full and wide outside off, asking Burns to go for the drive and Burns obliges but without any stride. Lucky not to edge it behind. A maiden to begin from Bumrah.
In the channel outside off, Burns offers no shot.
Bat on ball for the first time. This is fullish and just outside off, Burns comes on the front foot and pushes it towards the cover region.
Beats the outside edge this time! Perfect line and length and seems like Bumrah has found his rhythm. A length delivery just outside off, Burns pokes at it but makes no connection.
Gets closer this time and bowls this ball in the channel outside off. Burns lets it go to the keeper again.
A bit of a wayward start from Bumrah. A good length ball but it is way outside off. Burns lets it go to the keeper.

Right! We are done with all the pre-game formalities. It is indeed time for the action. The two umpires stride out in the middle first and they are followed by the Indian players. Matthew Wade and Joe Burns are the Aussie openers. Jasprit Bumrah will take the new ball for the Indians. Burns to face. Three slips and a gully in place. Here we go...
Before the action begins, it is time for the National Anthem of both the teams.

India (Playing XI) - Mayank Agarwal, Shubman Gill (TEST DEBUT) (IN FOR PRITHVI SHAW), Cheteshwar Pujara, Hanuma Vihari, Ajinkya Rahane (C), Rishabh Pant (WK) (IN FOR WRIDDHIMAN SAHA), Ravindra Jadeja (IN FOR VIRAT KOHLI), R Ashwin, Umesh Yadav, Jasprit Bumrah, Mohammad Siraj (TEST DEBUT) (IN FOR MOHAMMED SHAMI).

Indian skipper, Ajinkya Rahane, starts by saying that it is an honour for him to lead the side. On the first game, Rahane says that one hour of poor performance cost them the game. Wants the team to stay positive in this game. On two debutants, Rahane says that they have a good first-class record and he is excited for them. Says that they wanted to have an all-rounder and since Jadeja is fit, he is playing this game. Ends by telling that they would've batted first too.
Australia (Unchanged Playing XI) -Joe Burns, Matthew Wade, Marnus Labuschagne, Steve Smith, Travis Head, Cameron Green, Tim Paine (C/WK), Pat Cummins, Mitchell Starc, Nathan Lyon, Josh Hazlewood

Australian skipper, Tim Paine, starts by saying that half of their families are here so it was a quiet Christmas for them. On their win at Adelaide, Paine says that it was a good game for them but wants to focus on the series win. Tells that Warner is missed and adds he is pleased to know that he will be back for the third Test.
TOSS - Time for the flip of the coin. Australia skipper Tim Paine strides out along with Ajinkya Rahane. Up goes the coin and it lands in Paine's favor. Australia will BAT FIRST!

Hello, world! Ready for the big game? We are sure you are. It is Boxing Day time! Both the teams would look to end the year on a high. India have announced their XI already while the Aussies have indicated that they will be fielding the same XI too. How will India cope up without their talismanic skipper Kohli? How will the 2 debutants go about their business? Will Smith be able to get another big score at the MCG? How will Burns fare after a fine half ton in the 2nd innings last game? So many questions! We will get all the answers during the course of this game. Stay with us for the toss update!

Right! We are back for the second session! The Indian players are in a huddle near the rope. They now disperse to take their positions in the field. Joe Burns and Matthew Wade stride out to open the Aussie innings. In the first innings, Burns fell for a duck while Wade looked decent for his knock. They will have to play a big role if the Aussies are to get to a good score. Jasprit Bumrah will take the new ball for India. He was the one who gave the first wicket to the Indians. Rahane will want it from him again. Three men catching at slips, one at gully. Here we go...
... Day 3, Session 2 ...

Right! 131 is a good lead! And the way the Indians bowled in the first innings, they will be pretty confident to bundle the Aussies out again, to a small score. Australia, on the other hand, will need a good opening stand when they return for the second session. Join us for the same in a short while.

After getting the wicket of Rahane, the Aussies bowled short stuff at the Indians. Jadeja got out to Starc as he went after it. The Aussies continued bowling the same length to Ashwin and Yadav. They got them in the uncomfortable territory but they didn't get the breakthrough. It was a length ball from Hazlewood that got the wicket of Ashwin while Lyon removed the other two batters. In the end, Starc and Lyon ended up with a 3-fer while Cummins and Hazlewood got 2 and 1 respectively. Overall, it was a tough outing for the Aussies with the ball in this Indian innings

India started the day cautiously as Rahane and Jadeja negotiated the early overs easily. Jadeja in search of a quick single to get to his half ton ran out the skipper in a rather unfortunate fashion. However, he continued and got to his 50 eventually. He fell trying to take on the barrage of short stuff from Starc. Ashwin and Yadav copped a few blows on the body and eventually fell. Bumrah got out on the first ball but India have a decent lead.

Australia wrap up the innings quickly towards the end and they will take the honours of this session. They rattled the lower order with short stuff and eventually got the last 5 wickets for 32 runs. India, on the other hand, would be pleased with their 130 runs lead.

OUT! CAUGHT! Tossed up and around off and middle, Bumrah gets down and looks to play the slog sweep. He fails to connect it well and hits it high in the air. The deep square leg fielder, Head, runs to his left and takes the catch easily. India lead by 131 runs. With this wicket, it is Lunch on Day 3.
Length ball around off, Siraj looks to drive but gets an inside edge on the pad. The ball goes to point.
A bumper but it goes well over. Wided by the umpire.
Play and a miss! A length ball just around off, Siraj pokes at it away from his body to get beaten.
Mohammed Siraj is the last man in now.

OUT! CAUGHT! Hazlewood gets one now. His first in the game. A length ball outside off, Ashwin looks to drive but ends up getting it off the outer half. It goes just over Lyon who is at point. He makes no mistake and takes the catch easily. India lead by 130 runs.
Driven solidly but straight to the cover fielder.
Length ball around off, played towards gully.
Bouncer on middle and leg, Ashwin lets it be.
Who will walk out now? Will it be Bumrah or debutant Siraj? Bumrah it is.

OUT! CAUGHT! Lyon strikes and Yadav has to go. A tossed up ball outside off, the ball turns in. Yadav comes on the front foot and looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes straight to the slip fielder. Smith there makes no mistake. Just too good for the tail-ender.
Floated around middle, Yadav comes forward and defends.
Flat around off, Ashwin drives this one towards covers and takes a run.
Flatter around middle, defended towards short leg.
On middle, worked towards mid-wicket.
Flatter around middle, Yadav tucks it on the leg side and takes a run.
Shortish around middle,, tucked it towards fine leg for a single.
Shortish around middle, Yadav tried to pull but gets an inside edge on the pads.
Short ball around middle and leg, Yadav ducks under it.
A length ball just outside off, pushed towards point for a run.
Shorter this time outside off, Ashwin lets it go.
Length ball around off, Ashwin blocks this out.
Here's Josh Hazlewood for the first time on Day 3. Will he use the same tactics that Starc used?
Flatter and around off and middle, turned towards the forward short leg fielder.
Full and on middle and leg, flicked down to deep mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up and on middle, easily negotiated by Ashwin.
On off, defended back to the bowler.
Full and wide outside off, Ashwin strokes it through the covers and takes two. He will feel a lot comfortable playing the spinner.
Turned down leg after pitching, Ashwin nudges it to short fine leg.

An appeal for LBW but turned down! Starc changes plan and bowls a length ball. Yadav looks to hammer it down the ground but ends up getting an inside edge. An appeal from Starc but nothing from the umpire.
Ashwin has a word with Yadav. Probably telling him to play this one out.
And again! This time Umesh decides to duck under it.
Another short one, Yadav looks to pull but misses.
Pushes this one wide of the gully fielder and takes one.
Good length and around off, defended off the back foot.
Full and wide outside off, Yadav strokes it through covers for a run. Yadav wanted the second but Ashwin sends him back.
Flatter and on middle, kept out.
He now winds up for the massive slow but mistimes it towards deep mid-wicket for one.
Flatter outside off, defended towards covers.
Shorter this time turning in, Yadav plays it back to the bowler.
FOUR! The broom comes out now. Flatter ball around middle, Yadav sweeps it well wide of the man at deep square leg. No chance for him to cut it off.
Flatter around middle, worked on the on side for a run.
Another short ball. Yadav is late in getting down. This time he gets one on his shoulder. Rubs the area but doesn't show any sort of pain.
Length and outside off, pushed towards point for one.
Works this one down to deep square leg and opens his account.
Another short ball, this time to Umesh. He wanted a piece of it too but at the last second bailed out from going for the pull.
The response from Starc is another bumper! And Ashwin once again goes for the pull. Hits it down to deep square leg for one.
The Indian physio is out! Ashwin is looking in some pain. But he is a tough man as he puts the helmet and is ready to face.
Ouch! Ashwin gets a blow on the body now! And he calls for the physio straightaway. A short of a length ball airmed at the body, Ashwin looks to pull but gets hit on the chest.
Flatter around middle, tucked towards mid-wicket for a single.

Dropped! Labuschagne fails to hold onto another one. Flat and on middle and leg, Ashwin looks to pull but gets it off the inside edge. It goes to leg gully where Labuschagne gets both hands but fails to hold on.
Flatter ball on middle, Ashwin comes down and hits it straight to covers.
Floated around off, defended on the off side.
Tossed up and outside off, kept out.
Flatter around middle, tucked towards mid-wicket.
A sharp bumper to Yadav now! Nasty stuff from Starc here. He tried to get away but gets hit on the body.
Umesh Yadav walks in next.

OUT! CAUGHT! The short ball plan works and Jadeja falls prey to it. He was probably frustrated off the short stuff and tried to take on the bowler. Starc banged it in again. Jadeja pulled it hard but he found Cummins at deep mid-wicket. A good sliding take from him as this one was hit flat. Replays showed that he juggled and held onto it on the second attempt. Starc is elated. End of a fine knock from Jadeja. India's lead is 111 right now.
Play and a miss again! Starc has got is tail up. Lovely short ball that moves away a touch to beat the poke of Jadeja who is hoping around.
Outside off on a length, pushed to point.
Jadeja looks to go for it this time but he makes no connection.
Another sharp bumper from Starc. It is just outside off, Jadeja hops and tries to fend it off but misses.
Flatter around middle, Ashwin just plays it back to the bowler. Maiden to start after drinks.
Short of a length around middle, blocked on the backfoot.
Outside off this time, played towards covers.
Flatter around middle, Ashwin bunts this down.
Flatter around leg, defended on the on side.
Flat and on middle and leg, worked towards square leg.

DRINKS! A solid first hour for India but it would've gone to them completely had they not lost Rahane in an unfortunate way. But with the lead gone over 100 and 4 wickets still in the kitty, the Indians will feel they are in the driver's seat here. It has been hard work for Australia this morning. Good time for them to have this mini-break and work out a different plan. Let's see what they come up with.

A snorter of a delivery! A sharp bumper and Jadeja had no clue how to deal with it. Starc was appealing and he thought there was some bat or maybe gloves. The Aussie skipper has a word with him but they do not go for the review. A well-aimed bumper, Jadeja hops and tries to fend it off but it gets big on him and goes to the keeper. An appeal from the bowler but nothing from the umpire.
Back of a length and outside off, Jadeja leaves again.
Outside off, left alone by Jadeja.
Good running! A length ball on middle and leg, Jadeja clips it to the left of the deep square leg fielder for a brace.
Back of a length and on middle, worked to fine leg for one.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, Jadeja stays back to keep it out.
FOUR! Hammered! Another short ball, this time Jadeja rocks back and nails the pull down to the deep mid-wicket fence. Superb stroke and it brings up 300 for India.
Short now, worked towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up and outside off, turns away as Jadeja pokes it towards point.
Shortish and on middle, tucked towards square leg for one.
Fuller and around off, kept out.
Good ball to end the over! A shortish length just outside off, Jadeja thinks of playing at it but gets beaten.
Short of length around middle, pushed straight to covers.
Short of a length outside off, Jadeja just lets it go.
Shortish length on middle, poked towards point.
Short again on the body, Jadeja lets it be.
Shortish around middle, Jadeja pushes it towards point.
Bowling change! Mitchell Starc is back.
Flatter around middle, pushes on the on side for a single.
Short and wide, punched towards covers.
A tossed up ball just around off, defends it towards slip.
Flatter around middle, defended back.
Tosses up on middle, Jadeja blocks this out.
Tossed up outside off, pushed towards vovers for a single.
Bumper on the body, Jadeja is late in getting down. He gets hit on the body as the ball lobs to the keeper.
Length and around off, pushed towards cover.
Shortish and around off, blocked.
On the pads, Ashwin flicks it down to fine leg for a single to open his account.
A fuller ball around middle, flicked towards mid-wicket.

FIFTY FOR JADEJA! The Jadeja sword is out now and there goes the celebration. What an amazing art with the sword and even better with the willow in his hand. Such a valuable innings it has been from him. Came out in the middle, was welcomed with a few nasty bumpers but showed grit and determination and supported his skipper superbly. Ran him out just a while ago trying to get to the milestone but this time he flicks it down to fine leg for a single. The lead gets to 100 now. Time for him to get into the T20 mode?
Tossed up and turning in, Ashwin works it towards fine leg. End of a successful over for Australia.
Who is in next? Ravichandran Ashwin it is.
Run out appeal taken upstairs! Jadeja went for a quick single to get to his half ton but there is a run out appeal. Looks like Rahane is short. Yes! He is.

OUT! RUN OUT! Oh, dear! Rahane is short and he has to go. Australia get the big wicket. He just batted and batted and batted but now he falls trying to sneak a single to help his partner get to his half ton. But Jadeja will be stranded on 49 for now and Rahane goes after playing a brilliant knock. A flatter ball around off, Jadeja pokes it towards point and calls for a risky run. Skipper Rahane responds. Labuschagne quickly gets to the ball and fires the throw at the keeper's end. Paine collects and takes the bails off. The third umpire has been called for. Replays roll in and it shows Rahane is short, short by a few inches only but he has to go. Such a sad end to a fantastic knock for the skipper. He was involved in a run out in the first game with Kohli and now as a skipper, he gets dismissed that way. A classy knock from him and a class act as he walks back. He pats Jadeja and probably asks him to carry on! Terrific innings and terrific gesture. Standing ovation from the crowd for the skipper as he walks off.
Tossed up and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Shortish and just around off, Jadeja forces it towards point and thinks for a run but is sent back.
Full and on the pads, worked towards short fine leg for nothing.
Flat and wide outside off, Jadeja lets it go to the keeper.
Length ball around off, solidly defended towards the cover fielder.
Works this fuller ball on the pads to fine leg and moves to 49.
And another short ball but Jadeja has no problems dealing with it as he ducks.
Short and on middle, Jadeja sits under it.
Down the leg side. Left alone.
Shortish and around off, pushed towards covers.
Full and on the pads, worked towards short fine leg for nothing. 1 run from Lyon's first over in the morning.
On off, Rahane is solid in the defense on the front foot.
Shortish and just outside off, punched towards the cover fielder.
This time he clips it to the right side of the square leg fielder for one.
Flat and around off, Jadeja stays back to block.
Flatter and around off to begin, Jadeja keeps it out off his back foot.
Spin early on Day 3! Here's Nathan Lyon. 18-2-52-1 are his figures so far.
Play and a miss! Another short ball outside off, Rahane looks to cut but misses. Tried to actually play an upper cut but it was too close for that shot.
And finally a bumper for Rahane from Cummins. Rahane went after it and pulled it well but the square leg fielder dived to his right to make a stop.
Fullish this time and it is just outside off, Rahane defends it towards covers.
Landed around off, pushed towards Gully.
Angled in from outside off, Rahane looks to defend but is hit high on the pad.
Length ball just outside off, poked towards point. Says no for the run.
This time Rahane pushes it to mid off and calls for a quick single.
A solid front foot push to mid off from Rahane now.
Shortish and around off, kept out off the back foot.
Length ball outside off, Rahane lets it be.
Driven firmly again. This time it is to the right side of the cover fielder who makes a diving stop but Jadeja gets a single.
Fuller and around off, Jadeja drives it well but finds the cover fielder.
A single now as he flicks this fullish ball on middle to fine leg.

FOUR! Nicely done! A length ball just around off, Jadeja waits for it to get close and then looks to defend. The ball takes a thickish outside edge and goes to the left of gully. It races away to the third man fence.
In the channel outside off, left alone by Jadeja.
Length ball angled in, Jadeja looks to defend but gets an inside edge on the pad.
Back of a length and around middle, tucked down to deep square leg for one.
Outside off, left alone.
A bumper to Jadeja. He negotiates well by ducking under it.
Full and outside off, Rahane drives it on the up and through the covers. Returns for three before the fielder can chase it down. Fine shot.
On a length around off and middle, blocked.
First run for Jadeja in the morning. A length ball around off, Jadeja looks to defend but it takes the inner half and goes to mid-wicket. They cross for a single.
On the pads, Rahane flicks it down to deep square leg for a run.
Fuller and around off, nicely pushed but straight to mid off.
A maiden to begin from Cummins. Good length and around off, Jadeja defends it out from the crease.
A short ball but this is outside off. Jadeja has no issues sitting under it.
In the channel outside off, Jadeja shoulders arms.
Angled in and around off, pushed towards point.
A length ball around off, Jadeja comes on the front foot and pushes it towards mid off.
A nasty bumper from Cummins to begin! He runs in and bangs it short. It is right at the body. Jadeja does really well to duck under it. Paine collects well over his head.
Who will bowl from the other end? Pat Cummins it is. His figures are 22-7-71-2 so far.
Fuller and around off, pushed to mid off for nothing.
Runs for India and Rahane on Day 3! A shortish ball around middle, Rahane tucks it towards fine leg. Cummins from deep square leg runs to his right and makes a fine stop to save a couple of runs.
A good length ball around off to begin, Rahane stays back and pushes it towards gully.

Right! It is time for the action on Day 3. The two umpires make their way out to the middle and the Aussie players follow them to take their positions on the field. Indian skipper Ajinkya Rahane and Ravindra Jadeja stride out to the middle as well. Mitchell Starc is taking the ball. Well, he bowled just 3 balls when rain arrived and we were off a bit early. He will bowl to the Indian skipper. A bit of a defensive field setting. Just 1 fielder in the slip cordon. Here we go...

Shubhman Gill is caught for a quick chat before the action begins. Tells that the discussion was to get in and get a big partnership. Tells that he was a bit nervous at the start but was excited as well. Adds that he wanted to bat with intent and didn't want to get into the shell and miss out on scoring opportunities. On him and Jadeja going for the same catch, Gill says that he didn't hear the call from Jadeja and went for the catch. Says that he was happy that Jadeja held onto it. He says his cricket journey started at the age of 4 and later they moved to a different city where the facilities were better. Ends by saying that he has been along with the team for over a year or so but didn't expect a chance at the MCG.

What an amazing Day 2 it was for India! The skipper Rahane led from the front with a solid century while Jadeja showed superb maturity in his knock as well. The duo are not done yet and will arrive out in the middle to make merry of the Australian attack and give India a massive lead. The Aussies, on the other hand, will have to be on their toes and snaffle every chance that comes their way. The moving day of the Test match coming your way shortly.
... Day 3, Session 1 ...

Right! That's all from Day 2! India with the lead of 82 runs and 5 wickets in the pocket are well and truly on top! On Day 3, Rahane and Jadeja will look to continue batting and grow the lead as big as they could. Australia, on the other hand, will get under the pump after every single run from here. They will have to take the remaining 5 wickets quickly or else the game might go beyond their reach. The action on Day 3 will begin at 1030 local (2330 GMT Previous Day). We will look for your company again. Until then, take care!

The Aussies were relentless with the ball but they just couldn't get past the challenge of Rahane and Jadeja. A few chances came their way but they failed to hold onto them. Cummins was superb in the first session and was rewarded with two wickets in Gill and Pujara. Things didn't go their way after that as Vihari and Pant played handy little knocks and eventually Rahane and Jadeja stuck to the plan and didn't allow them another sniff.

The day started with Gill playing a few delightful strokes before falling in an attempt of playing a booming cover drive. Pujara followed him back to the pavilion. However, skipper Rahane joined Vihari and added 50-plus. He did the same with Pant after Vihari fell trying to dominate Lyon. Pant too departed after a short knock but Rahane continued. He got another able partner, this time in Jadeja who just grew in confidence after every ball. The two will return to make the most of it on the moving day of the Test.

What an enthralling day's play! Take a bow, Ajinkya Rahane. It is India who have their noses well ahead in this game now! The Indian skipper has led from the front and taken the team to a very good position with this fabulous unbeaten century. Credit to Jadeja for staying in with him and at the same time, he kept the scoreboard ticking as well. The duo have added 88 runs in this final session and are still going strong.
So, that will be it from Day 2! We could've had a few more overs if not for the rain but it has arrived at a perfect time for the Indians. It is STUMPS ON DAY 2.

The Indian physio is out again! Rahane again, got the blow on his gloves, on the last ball is getting the treatment. And looks like the rain has made its appearance again it seems. The covers are coming on at the moment and the players are walking off.

Put down! Oh, dear, Australia! What is happening? Head cannot believe that he has put it down. Another chance goes begging. A sharp bumper around off, Rahane looks to defend off his toes but he is not in control as it flies to his right off the gloves. Head from point comes running forward and so does Green from gully. Both go for it but Head lunges forward first and then gets both his hands on the ball but as his elbows land on the turf, the ball pops out. A let off for Rahane here.
Fulller length around off, pushed towards covers.
Full ball outside off, driven to the right of mid off for a run.
Here's Mitchell Starc. 18-3-60-2 from him so far.
Fuller length ball outside off, Jadeja taps it towards deep point for a run.
Shortish ball just outside off, Jadeja sways away from it.
Fuller ball but way outside off, ignored by Jadeja.
Fuller length ball outside the off stump, Jadeja lets it be.
Jadeja lets it go to the keeper.
WIDE! Short and way outside off, wided by the umpire.
Cameron Green again. 11-1-29-0 from him so far.
Length ball around middle, played straight back.
Again short and wide, played toward deep point for a run.
Short and wide, Jadeja punches this one towards covers.
Tossed up ball on the stumps, blocked solidly.
A shortish ball outside off, played towards point.
Floated around off, defended solidly.
Floated around off, defended back.
Change in bowling. Here's Nathan Lyon again.

FOUR! Classy drive this by Rahane. A fuller length ball around off, Rahane creams this drive through the covers. The boundary brings up 100-run stand between the two. This can well be a match-winning stand between the two.
Length ball on the stumps, tucked towards square leg for a run.
Bumper on the body, Jadeja ducks under it.
Length ball in the channel outside off, left alone by Jadeja.
Overpitched outside off, squeezed towards point.
Fulller length ball around off, blocked solidly.
The Indian physio is out there! Rahane gets the chance to gather is thoughs again after that century.
Shortish and around off, Rahane manages to fend it off as it bounces extra. Maybe he has taken a blow on the gloves.
Back of a length ball around off, kept out.

FOUR! SHOT! CENTURY FOR RAHANE! What a sensational knock this has been from him! He has batted with ease here. The big pressure of leading India in the absence of  their regular skipper Kohli has not put him under any sort of pressure. If at all it has done anything, it has helped his game. There were questions about his form which has dipped over the past couple of years but he has responded with a superb gritty knock. He gets a loosener from Cummins. Short and wide outside off, Rahane slashes it over point and bags the boundary to get to the milestone. His 12th Test ton. He has repeated his Melbourne heroics form 2014 here and is putting the team in a great position. A sedate celebration from him as he knows that the job his not finished.
An appeal for LBW but only from behind the wicket. Nothing from Cummins. It comes back in after pitching. Rahane misses to get hit on the pad. Replays show a big inside edge.
Around off again, tapped towards gully.
Around off on a length, a solid front foot defense from Rahane.
And another leave it is from Jadeja as Josh bowls it wide outside off.
Just outside off on a good length. A brave leave from Jadeja.
Three more and Rahane is just a boundary away from a ton! He gets a fuller ball on the pads and flicks it through square leg. Good, aggressive running means they get three.
Length ball around off, Rahane looks to work it on the leg side but the ball takes the outer half and goes towards point.
Fuller and around off, driven to mid off.
Shortish and around off, poked towards point.
Tucked towards the leg side for a single. Rahane will keep the strike for the next over.
Banged short and Rahane pulls it wide of the man at deep mid-wicket. Two more for Rahane.
The gully fielder makes a stop now. A shortish ball just outside off, Rahane stays back and forces it to the left of Green at gully who makes a diving stop.
Stunning stroke but Wade makes an excellent save! Fuller and outside off, Rahane drills the drive but Wade dives to his right to knock it down.
Back of a length and around middle, tucked through square leg for one.
Length ball around off, Rahane looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half and goes to fine leg for a run.
A maiden to begin from Hazlewood in his fresh spell but nothing threatening. A length ball outside off, left alone.
A bumper now! Jadeja once again sways away and allows for Paine to collect.
Outside off again from Josh. Jadeja lets it be.
On the pads, flicked through mid-wicket for a brace by Jadeja.
Fullish but outside off again, easily left alone.
A length ball outside off to begin from him, Jadeja lets it be.
Change in bowling. Josh Hazlewood returns. His figures are 18-6-34-0 so far.
Length ball around off, defended solidly by Rahane.
Length ball around middle, tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball around middle and leg, Jadeja misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. Huge appeal from the bowler but nothing from the Umpire.
Good length around off angling across, Jadeja withdraws from his defense.
A length ball around off, Rahane plays it gently past the gully fielder for a single. They think for two but decided against it.
Length ball around middle, tucks this one towards fine leg for a run.

FOUR! Take that! Short and wide outside off, Rahane hammers it over point and bags another boundary. Runs flowing thick and fast for the Indians now. Rahane moves to 88 with that boundary and India crosses 250.
Short of a length but again down leg, left alone by Rahane.
Length ball down the leg, Rahane misses his flick.
Play and a Miss by Rahane, A fuller length ball outside off, Rahane looks to drive but gets beaten.
Good Running this by the two! A length ball around middle, Rahane tucks this one towards fine leg and takes a quick couple of runs. Starc is not happy with the fielder there.
Length ball on off, Jadeja taps this towards mid on and takes a quick run. The single brings up the lead to 50.
Back of a length and around off, kept out.
Two more! Short and wide outside off, he punches it through the cover region for a brace now.
Similar length, Similar short, driven nicely down the ground but this time Marnus keeps it to two. Rahane is looking good against the new ball as he is presenting the full face of the bat.
FOUR! Nicely driven! A fullish ball outside off, Rahane leans on the drive and the ball races past mid off. Marnus chases the ball but loses the race.
Good length around off, played towards covers.
Length ball around off, Rahane dabs it on the off side.
Pat Cummins to bowl with the second new ball from the other end.

India ahead in this game now with a decent lead already! Rahane is looking solid out in the middle while Jadeja is doing his job superbly. Australia have taken the second new ball. And they would want it to use it well and get the breakthrough quickly. Interesting final phase coming up on Day 2.
Lovely delivery to end the over! Just outside off and angled in, Jadeja pokes at it but misses.
Wide outside off, left alone.
In the channel outside off, Jadeja lets it go to the keeper.

PUT DOWN?. That went really quickly to Smith but it burst through his fingers. A full ball outside off, Rahane looks to squeeze it out but gets it off the outside edge. It goes towards the left of Smith at a good height but he is taken by surprise as it comes quickly to him and he fails to hold on.
Full again, Rahane drives it towards the cover region.
A fuller one on the pads of Jadeja to beign, he whips it through mid-wicket for three.

The second new ball is due now! You would assume they will take it straightaway. Looks like it as the reserve umpire comes running towards the onfield umpire to hand over the ball. Mitchell Starc will use the ball first. He had struck in the first over with the new ball in the first innings. Can he do something similar here? Here he goes.
Tossed up and around off, a big stride forward and Rahane is solid on the front foot.
Another loopy ball around off, kept out by Rahane.
Tosses it up and Rahane is on the front foot to defend.
Flatter and around off, kept out.
Nice short. Wide outside off from Lyon. It has been the line he is bowling from the last two overs. This time Jadeja crunches it through backward point for three.
Full and on middle, flicked wide of the man at mid on for a single.
Flicks the next one through mid-wicket and gets two.
In the channel outside off, a leave from Jadeja.
Bumper to Jadeja now but it goes well over.
Short and on middle, pulled down to fine leg for a run.
Another fine shot but nothing again. Full and wide outside off, Rahane drives but the cover fielder makes a diving stop to his left.
Full around off, driven to mid off.
Another short ball outside off, Jadeja finds cover again. A maiden from Lyon.
Tossed up and outside off, turning away. A leave from Jadeja.
Floated full and around off, Jadeja pushes it towards gully and thinks for a single but is sent back.
Short again, punched towards mid off.
Tossed up around off, Jadeja comes on the front foot to block.
Short and wide outside off, Jadeja cuts but can't go past the backward point fielder.
Fuller length around off, Rahane pushes this one towards cover.
Shortish ball on the stumps, Rahane bunts this on the off side.
A fuller length this time outside off swings away, Rahane leaves it alone.
Length ball outside off, shouldered arms by Rahane.
Fullish ball outside off, driven nicely but straight to mid off.
Full and on middle, flicked wide of the man at mid on for a quick single.
Floated on middle, tucked towards mid-wicket. Good over from Lyon.
Slightly short on the stumps, played straight back.
Tossed up around off, tucked away towards backward square leg.
Floated around middle, tucked towards fine leg for single.
Beaten by the flight. A tossed up ball around off, Jadeja looks to defend but gets beaten. That was a beautiful ball from Lyon.
Tossed up and outside off, turning away. Jadeja lets it be.
Short and just outside off, Rahane looks to cut but misses.
Another one well outside off, Rahane is not playing at it.
Outside off, a leave from Rahane.
Landed around off on a length, pushed towards the off side.
Pushes the next fuller one towards mid off for one. And the single brings up yet another 50-run stand.
FOUR! SHOT! Short and wide outside off, Jadeja slams it through backward point and bags a boundary.
Fuller ball on middle, swept away towards fine leg for a single.
Flatter around off, blocked by Jadeja.
Floated ball around off, jadeja leaves it alone, was close to the off stump.
Floated around middle, tucked towards square leg for a run.
Jadeja punches it through the covers for a single.
Tossed up outside off, Jadeja lets it go. The ball turned sharply after pitching.
Back of a length on the body, Jadeja nudges it towards square leg and takes a quick single.
In the channel outside off, Jadeja lets it go to the keeper.
Fuller and around middle, Jadeja stays back to block.
Outside off, watchfully left alone.
Back of a length and around off, kept out.
Full ball down the leg side. Jadeja misses his flick.
Change from the other end too! Here's Cameron Green. 7-1-19-0 from him so far.
Shortish and around off, Rahane goes back to block it out. 6 off Lyon's over.
Floated around middle, pushed back to Lyon.
FOUR! DRILLED! Stunning stroke! Lyon tosses it up, Rahane jumps out of the crease and nails the drive through the covers. Cummins gives it a chase till the ropes, dives and tries to stop but misses.
Flatter and on middle, worked towards mid-wicket.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.

He starts with a shortish ball outside off, Rahane punches it to the left of the cover fielder who dives that side but fails to stop. The point fielder runs to get to the ball. Enough time for Rahane to take two more.
Time for spin again! Nathan Lyon is back on. 12-1-37-1 from him.
A length ball around off, Jadeja dabs it towards gully.
Short ball around leg stump, Jadeja ducks under it.
A drive enticing ball outside off, Jadeja leaves it.
Fuller this time angling around middle, Jadeja plays it with a straight bat towards mid on.
A length ball outside off, driven by Jadeja to the covers.
Shortish outside off, Jadeja punches this one towards point.
Good leave by Rahane, A length ball outside off, Rahane does not tinker with it.
Length ball angling across, Rahane leaves it alone.
A couple now to Rahane. A short ball outside off, Rahane punches this one through the covers and collects a couple.
Length ball on middle, Rahane comes forward and defends it.
Fuller ball angling in the pads, Rahane flicks this one wide towards mid on.
Fuller length around off, Rahane pushes this one towards covers.
Fuller ball this time but down the leg side, Jadeja misses his flick and the keeper dives and stops the ball.
Length ball outside off, Jadeja pushes this one at cover.
Shortish ball around middle, Rahane pulls this one towards deep square leg for a single.
Short of a length on the body, Rahane tucks it on the on side.
Three more! Again not from the middle of Jadeja's bat. A length ball outside off, Jadeja plays at it away from his body. The ball flies through gully and they take three.
Length ball around off, blocked by Jadeja.
Length ball to finish the over, outside off stump and left alone.

EDGY FOUR! Lucky for Rahane! A length ball outside off, Rahane flirts with it as he stays rooted to his crease. An outside edge is induced but it flies between the keeper and Smith who is at the second slip. Rahane into the 60s. 200 up for the visitors. The lead now reads 7.
Shortish ball on the body, Rahane stands tall and bunts it down.
Fuller ball but way outside off, left alone.
Beaten! A length ball around off, held its line and Rahane tries to defend but is beaten on the outside edge.
Good length angling across, Rahane leaves it alone.
Maiden from Hazlewood. A short ball this time around off, Jadeja has no business playing with it.
A short bumper on the body, Jadeja ducks under it.
A length ball in the corridor outside off, Jadeja shoulders arms to it.
Shortish around middle, Jadeja dabs it on the on side.
Short of a length on middle, blocked solidly.
Length ball angling across, Jadeja leaves it alone.
Another one down the leg side and Rahane misses his flick again.

Appeal for caught behind down the leg side but nothing from the umpire. A fuller ball down the leg side, Rahane misses his flick. Paine dives to his right and collects the ball. He appeals but not out says the umpire.
Length ball around off, pushed towards point.
STREAKY FOUR! A length ball just around off. It shapes away. Rahane plays it very late and runs it down to the third man fence. India take the lead with that boundary.
Fuller and around off, Rahane blocks.
Length ball around off, Jadeja pushes it towards the off side crosses for a quick single.
Bumper on middle, Jadeja takes it on and pulls it wide of the fine leg fielder.
Shortish and around off, Jadeja blocks off the back foot.
Fuller and around off, Jadeja looks to flick but gets a leading edge back to the bowler.
Steven Smith is shadow practicing! Yes. He is in the middle to field but he is not missing out on the chance to practice. Hasn't been best of the series for him and he would like to get back to form.
A short ball on middle, Jadeja ducks.
Back of a length and around off, it keeps low as Jadeja is hit on the pad. They appeal but nothing from the umpire. Clearly a big inside edge on this one.
Good length and around off, Jadeja pushes it towards the off side and thinks for a run but Rahane sends him back.
Who will take the ball from the other end? Josh Hazlewood it is. He is still searching for his first wicket in this game.
Banged short and Jadeja says enough is enough. He rocks back and pulls it wide of the man at mid on. Three taken before the fielder can get to the ball.
Good length and around off, kept out off the front foot.
In the channel outside off, left alone.

Right! The rain is gone! The players are back out in the middle. Jadeja batting on 4 will face Mitchell Starc who will complete his over. India are 6 behind the Aussie score of the first inning. Two slips, one leg gully  and a forward short leg. You know what the plan is. Here we go...
... Day 2, Final session ...
UPDATE 1532 local (0432 GMT) - Good news! The covers are coming off. We will begin the final session at 1545 local which is just over 10 minutes away.

The Aussie bowlers failed to put pressure on the Indians in this session as Vihari and Pant went after the bowlers and scored freely with Rahane standing there like a rock. Lyon got a decent purchase from the wicket and removed Vihari while Starc got better of Pant. However, the task is not done yet for the Aussies. They need to strike early in the final session or else the Indians will be able to take a decisive lead. Join us for the final session in a short while.

2 wickets in the session but India have scored 99 runs and they are just 6 behind which means the session has gone to the visitors. It was Vihari who looked good but fell in his attempt of taking on the spinner. However, Rahane along with Pant added 57 to push the Aussies on the back foot. Like Vihari, Pant too fell but Rahane has kept going and he is been proving to be the thorn in the flesh for the Aussies. He has reached a well-composed half ton and would look to carry on along with Jadeja.
And the umpire's have called for the TEA! It was around the corner anyway. So, let's hope when we return, we are back with the game.
Rain around the corner and the covers are coming on! There was a prediction for rain and it has arrived.
Sharp again from Starc. This one is around off, Jadeja hops and keeps it out.
FOUR BYES! Starc is trying to rattle Jadeja with the bumper on the body but on this one he does little too much. It goes wide of leaping Paine and into the fine leg fence.
Down the leg side. Jadeja looks to flick but misses.
Full ball on middle, Rahane flicks it towards square leg.
A good length ball around off, a bit of inswing, Rahane blocks this one on the on side.
Fuller length ball around middle, Rahane defends it solidly.
A good length ball around off, pushed on the off side.
Short ball angling into Rahane, who ducks under it.
Short of a length, Jadeja dabs it towards point for a run.
Full and outside off, pushed towards point.
FOUR BYES! Starc goes for the yorker but bowls it down the leg side. Rahane fails to flick it. Paine dives to his left but fails to collect the ball.
One more leave as Starc continues to bowl in the channel.
Another one wide outside off, easily allowed it to go to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR RAHANE! The skipper is leading the charge for the Indians here. A fine knock from him. There were murmurs regarding his form with the bat but he has played a well-compiled knock to put all the talks to rest. Can he take India to a stronger position from here? He got a superb hundred in the 2014/15 tour and would be eager to do something similar here. He gets to his half ton by flicking the fuller ball on his pads down to the fine leg fence.
Good over this from Cummins. A shortish ball but down the leg, Jadeja leaves it alone.
Another one of those short balls on the body, Jadeja ducks again.
Shortish ball on leg, dabs it down on the on side.
Short of a length around off,  Jadeja sways away from it.
Another short one on the body, Jadeja ducks under it.
Shortish ball on the body, Jadeja dabs it towards the slips.
Change in bowling. Pat Cummins returns. 16-6-50-2 are his numbers so far.

Nicely punched and Jadeja gets three to open his account. Fuller and around off, Jadeja meets it with straight bat and pushes it through mid off. The fielder from the ring chases it down. Three taken. Successful over from Starc.
Outside off, Jadeja lets it go to the keeper.
Length ball around off, Jadeja defends off his back foot.
Fuller and around off, blocked off the front foot by Jadeja.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Who comes in now? Ashwin or Jadeja? The latter it is. He is playing his 50th Test match here.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A poor, poor short from Pant and he throws it away. Starc gets the timely breakthrough. Short and just wide outside off, Pant throws his bat as he looks to cut but ends up getting a tickle behind. Paine accepts the catch and celebrates. It wasn't that wide but Pant wanted a peice of it but he falls in the process. 250th Test wicket for Starc. A good, little hand though from Pant. India still behind 22.
A length ball just around off, pushed towards covers. Rahane has to wait for his 50.
Short ball on middle, Rahane pulls this one through the gap at deep mid-wicket and collects a couple.
A length ball in the channel outside off, left alone.
Good yorker but Rahane is up for it as he keeps it out easily.
Around off on a length, pushed towards point.
Short ball outside off, Rahane lets it go. It was good bumper which Paine jumps and collects.
Single on the last ball as Rahane pushes it wide of the cover fielder. They wanted the second but opted against it in the end.
Length ball on the pads, Pant flicks it down to deep square leg for one.
A yorker on middle, Pant jams it down.

Shot! Fine shot! Fuller and around off, Rahane comes on the front foot and pushes it through the covers. Just a mere push. The cover fielder chases it down. Three taken as Labuschagne makes a sliding stop.
Fuller and around middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Wide outside off to begin, Rahane lets it go to the keeper.
Bowling change! Starc is back. Can he rattle Pant with a few bumpers? 9-3-23-1 from him so far.
Pant batting way out of his crease makes a solid front foot defense on the last ball.
On the pads, worked down to deep square leg for one. Another 50-run stand for India.
A front foot block to follow the boundary.
FOUR! A freebie from Green! A friendly full toss, Rahane just pushes it down the ground. Just timed it and it raced to the long on fence. The skipper moves into the 40s.
Length ball around middle, worked on the leg side for nothing.
Good length and just around off, poked towards point.
Cameron Green gets to bowl now. 5-1-12-0 from him so far.

Chance but Green misses to hold on! Cummins lures Pant with a fuller ball outside of, Pant goes after it and it flies off the outer half towards Green at gully. He dives to his left, sticks out his one hand but it doesn't stick. Two taken as the ball goes to deep point.
Banged short and Pant pulls it through mid-wicket. Deep square leg fielder gets around but not before Pant adds two more to his name.
Fuller ball around off, Pant hits it straight back to the bowler, Cummins there picks the ball in his follow through and has a shy at the keeper's end but misses. Good fielding there by Cummins.
Fuller ball around off, Pant drives it to the covers.
Length ball wide outside off, Pant lets it be.
Wide outside off on a length, easily left alone by Pant.

A couple to end the over! It pitches outside off again and turns in. Not too much as Rahane looks to cut but it bounces extra. The India skipper manages to guide it fine towards third man for a brace.
Turning in from outside off from a shortish length. Rahane keeps it out.
Fuller and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Short on the body, Rahane pulls this one past fine leg to collect a couple, where Wade collects the ball and stops the boundary.
Floated around middle, tucked on the on side.
Short and outside off, gets a bottom edge and almost chops it on.
Fuller and on middle, Pant flicks this time but finds mid on. A maiden from Cummins after going for 12 in his previous over.
Gets the line to the bumper right. Pant sways away from the line. Good over from Cummins so far. Pant has responded well too as he has kept himself calm and has not gone after him.
Cummins bends his back and this time goes for a bumper but the line is down the leg side. Pant ducks easily.
One more leave as Cummins continues to bowl in the channel. He is not giving away anything in this over here.
Another one wide outside off, Pant has no business with it as he shoulders arms.
In the channel outside off, Pant lets it go to the keeper.
Shortish and outside off, turns back in as Rahane tucks it towards short fine leg.
On middle, Rahane defends it out off his front foot.
Short and wide again, Pant cuts it hard again. This time the cover-point fielder runs to his left and keeps it down to a run.
FOUR! Slammed away! Pant is in mood here as he bags another boundary. Short and just outside off, Pant rocks back and flays it through the covers for a boundary. 150 is up for the Indians.
Full and around off, blocked off the front foot.
Full and on middle and leg, Rahane comes down the track and pokes it to mid-wicket for a single.
Good from Rahane! He had a word with Pant just after the 5th ball of the over. Maybe just wanted to calm him down a bit.
A fullish ball wide of the crease from Cummins, Pant pushes it towards the cover region. Excellent over for the Indians.

FOUR! Through the off side. Pant bags another boundary. A fuller ball outside off, Pant goes for the drive. It is not off the middle but it goes wide of the backward point fielder for a boundary. The deficit now is under 50.
Cummins returns back to bowling in the channel outside off now and Pant says I am not playing at these.
FOUR! A boundary now! Pat runs in and bangs it short and bowls it on middle, Pant swivels and nails the pull in front of square for a boundary. Super shot. 8 off the first 3 balls.
This time he hits it wide of the cover fielder. Two more before the mid off fielder can get to the ball.
Full and around off, Pant drives it down the ground. He fails to connect it sweetly but it goes towards long off. Two taken.

Exciting first hour of the second session! India will feel they have their noses ahead but by just. They started the session well but Vihari fell trying to go after Lyon. Rahane has looked good and he needs to continue if India are to push for a lead. Pant too has looked decent but he too needs to carry one. Australia, on the other hand, needs to send Rahane back in the pavilion as soon as they can. Let's see how things pan out in the second half of the second session.
Dot to end! Flatter and around middle and leg, Rahane stays back and defends it out.
On middle, kept out by Rahane off the front foot.
Floated on middle, defended back to the bowler.
This time he pushes it wide of the short cover fielder for one.
And again! Pant lets it be once again.
Tossed up and outside off, turning away. Pant lets it be.

FOUR! Nicely done by Rahane! A good over for the Indians as they get 8 off it. Cummins bowls a very full ball outside off, Rahane squeezes it between gully and the slip cordon. The ball races away to the third man fence.
Rahane drives this through the covers for another couple as Labuschagne chases the ball and returns it back.
A fuller length around middle, defended solidly on the off side.
Length ball outside off, Rahane shoulders arms to it.
Shortish ball outside off, Rahane stands tall and punches this through the covers for a brace.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Change in bowling. Pat Cummins is back on. 12-5-26-2 from him so far.
Tossed up around off, Pant keeps it out with a solid front foot defense.
Rahane skips down the track and flicks it down to deep square leg for one.
Floated around off, Pant punches it to mid off and gets to the other end.
Lands on middle and turns in. Pant nudges it to fine leg and takes two.
Short and wide, Pant cuts it hard but finds cover-point.
Two slips in place now for Pant.
Wide outside off, pushed towards the cover region.
Good length ball around off, defended solidly.
Fuller ball around middle, Rahane blocks this out on the front foot.
Shortish outside off, pulled down to mid-wicket.
Fuller ball in the channel outside off, Rahane leaves it alone.
Short of a length outside off, dabs it towards point.
A ripper! Landed just around off and then shaped away. Rahane looks to defend off his toes but misses.
Flat and around off, Rahane pushes it towards short third man and gets to the other end.
Short and wide, Pant cuts it to cover-point and takes a run.
Lands outside off and turns away as Pant lets it go to the keeper.

Edgy! Pant is off the mark in a streaky fashion! Tossed up again and this one is full. It turns away as Pant comes on the front foot to defend. It takes the outside edge and goes past Smith at first slip. He gives it a chase and keeps it down to two.
Rahane comes down the track and covers the spin and pushes it towards mid on for one.
Tossed up around middle, turning in, tucked on the leg side by Rahane.
Bumper to end the over. A short ball on the body, Pant ducks under it.
Good length ball angling across Pant, he lets it be.
Fuller length ball on the pads, flicked away towards square leg for a single.
Something has got in the eyes of Hazlewood. He is getting helped by his bowling partner Cummins. He is ready now.
Short ball on middle, Rahane sways away from it. Hazlewood gives a stare!
Length ball around off, guided it towards gully.
Good length ball around middle, Rahane block this out.
Another one which is bowled outside off, Pant lets it be again. End of a successful over from Lyon.
Darted outside off, Pant shoulders arms.
Risabh Pant strides out in the middle, replacing Hanuma Vihari.

OUT! CAUGHT! Lyon strikes! Vihari wanted to dominate the spinner but falls in the process. Lyon wins the battle. A tossed up ball on middle, Vihari winds up and goes for the slog sweep but the ball bounces extra and takes the gloves. It balloons to the left of the keeper. The first slip fielder, Smith, calls for the catch and takes it easily. They appeal and the finger is raised. Lyon gets his man and breaks the blooming stand. Shake of the head as Vihari walks back. India needed him to continue. India still behind 79.

FOUR! Shot! Fine shot from Vihari. A flatter ball outside off, Vihari stays back, waits for the ball to get closer and then cuts it through short third man for a boundary. It brings up the 50-run stand between the two.
Shortish around off, tucked away towards mid-wicket.
Floated around off, Vihari sweeps but finds backward square leg.
