The Indian physio is out in the middle. It is Rahane who is getting some attention. Some issue with his back it seems. The two umpires are having a word with him now as he gets up and is ready to face again.
Dot to end! In the channel outside off, Rahane allows it to go to the keeper. 7 from the over.
Uppish but safe! Back of a length ball on middle, Vihari goes for the pull. He doesn't go full swing and it goes wide of the fine leg fielder for one.
Fuller and just outside off, defended towards the cover region.
Works the next one through square leg to get to the other end.
A jaffa from Hazlewood. Good comeback from him. Shortish and around off, it shapes away nicely as it gets close to the bat of Rahane who looks to defend. Lucky not to edge.
FOUR! Banged short and Rahane says I am ready for that. He swivels and nails the pull down to the deep square leg fence. Fine shot.
No ball! A length ball outside off, Rahane lets it be. The third umpire from upstairs calls it a no ball.
Pitches outside off, turns in again as Vihari looks to work it on the leg side. The ball hits his pad and goes over leg gully fielder. Two leg byes taken.
Flat and on middle, tucked to square leg for nothing.
On middle, pushed to mid on for a quick single.
Flaoted around middle, Rahane plays it back to the bowler.
Around off stump, Rahane prods forward to defend it.
Floated on middle, Rahane looks to defend but it goes to leg slip off the inner half.
Dot to end the over. A length ball outside off, left alone.
Fuller length on middle, Vihari blocks this one on the on side.
Short of a length around off, Rahane pulls it towards fine leg for another single.
Fuller this time around middle and leg, flicked towards fine leg for a single.
Good length and around off, defended towards mid on.
Back of a length and on middle, Vihari gets on his toes to defend.
Good turn again! Rahane manages to keep it out at the very last moment. This one pitches outside off and turns back in. Rahane is on his back foot and gets his bat down in time to keep it out.
Full and on middle, flicked well but Rahane finds mid on.
Shortish and on middle, Vihari nudges it towards square leg for a single. 100 up for India with that run.

FOUR BYES! That beats everyone. Tossed up just outside off, it pitches, bounces extra and turns way down the leg side. No chance for Paine to stop that as it races down to the fine leg fence for four byes.
On off, Vihari flicks but finds mid-wicket.
Tossed up and on middle, Rahane flicks it through mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Fuller ball outside off, left alone.
Fullish ball around middle, defended straight back.
Short ball around off stump, Vihari ducks under it.
A length ball around middle, taps it towards mid-wicket and takes a quick run.
A length ball on middle, Rahane blocks this out.
Fuller ball around off, defended towards covers.
Short and on middle, Rahane goes for the pull but doesn't connect it as well as he would've liked. It goes to the left of Starc at square leg. They take a run.
Flat and on middle, worked towards the square leg region for one.
Flatter and outside off, Rahane punches it wide of the man at point and takes a single.
Fuller and around off, kept out by Rahane off the front foot.
Around off, turning in to Rahane who does well to block.
Flatter ball on the pads, Rahane comes on the front foot to defend but pads it away in the end.
Who will bowl fron the other end?  Lyon it is. His figures are 3-1-7-0 so far.
A maiden to begin the session from Hazlewood. Length ball around off, Vihari once again is on his toes to defend it.
Another one around off, Vihari stays back to defend.
Bowls this length ball on the stumps and Vihari comes on the front foot to block.
Outside off on a good length again, Vihari shoulders arms.
Slightly fuller but still wide enough for Vihar to play.
Hazlewood starts with a length ball outside off which shapes away further outside off. Vihari lets it go to the keeper.

We are back for the 2nd session! The Aussie players walk out to the middle to take their positions on the field. Ajinkya Rahane and Hanuma Vihari make their way out in the middle as well. Josh Hazlewood has the ball to begin the session for Australia. Here we go...
... Day 2, Session 2 ...

Right! A brilliant session of play is over but another interesting one awaits. India will want their skipper to play big innings and others to support. The Aussies, on the other hand, would be looking to strike early in the second session to force India further on the back foot. Join us for the second session in a short while.

Australians toiled hard in the first hour. They had a review on the very first ball of the day but it didn't go their way and then the next over saw Paine put down a chance. There were a few more chances but they didn't carry to the fielders. However, Cummins finally got the reward when he struck twice in two overs to remove both the overnight batters. They didn't get another success in the next hour but they have kept things really tight.

An absorbing session of play! India started Day 2 well as Gill and Pujara almost saw off the first hour of play with Gill playing a couple of delightful strokes. However, both fell before the Drinks break in consecutive overs of Cummins. Skipper Rahane and Vihari then made sure there wasn't another wicket lost in the session as they added 26 in the process.

Full and around off, turns in a touch as Rahane looks to defend. He gets it off the inner half. The ball goes just to the right of the forward short leg fielder. Wasn't too far but Rahane survives. With that, it is Lunch on Day 2.
On middle, Rahane is solid in defense.
Floated on middle, this time Vihari works it wide of the man at mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Tossed up and around off and middle, Vihar blocks it off the front foot.
On middle, tucked on the leg side.
Down the leg side. Left alone.
Fuller and outside off, Rahane squeezes it out towards gully where the fielder does well to stop the ball to his right.
On the pads and Rahane flicks it wide of the mid-wicket fielder who chases it down. Two taken before he can get to the ball.
Full but outside off, Rahane covers the stumps and allows it to Paine behind.
Sharp short of a length ball just around off, it is angling away. Rahane sways out of the line.
Length ball just outside off, pushed towards mid off by Rahane.
Short and wide outside off, Rahane lets it be.
Flatter and on middle again, Vihari keeps it out. Maiden to start from Lyon.
Looks to come down the track again but this time Lyon bowls it flat. Vihari adjusts well and tucks it on the leg side.
On middle, worked on the leg side.
This time he stays inside the crease, a big stride forward and a solid defense.
Comes down the track does Vihari and looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get struck on the pad.
A floated fuller ball around off, Vihari comes on the front foot and pushes it back to the bowler.
Spin for the first time. Here's GOAT, Nathan Lyon!
Another fuller ball but this time Rahane is not chasing after it as he shoulders arms.
A full ball outside off, Rahane looks to drive but misses and the ball goes through to Paine.
Full and on middle, flicked on the leg side.

FOUR! Streaky boundary for Rahane. A length ball around off, the ball pitches and then moves away as Rahane looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge. It goes past the gully fielder and into the third man fence.
Length ball around off, Rahane comes on the front foot to defend.
Length ball around off, kept out.
Bouncer on middle. Vihari ducks.
Little too wide outside off, easy leave.
Fuller and around off, blocked off the front foot.
Full and on the pads, clipped to fine leg for one.
Back of a length and around off, Rahane gets on his back foot to block.
Fullish and around off, Rahane comes on the front foot to keep it out.
Full and on the pads, flicked to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Yorker length ball on the pads, Vihari misses his flick and they take a leg bye. Loud appeal from Starc, but the Umpire is not interested neither is Paine convinced to go for the review.
Length ball outside off, Vihari lets it be.
Fullish ball around off, Vihari drives it straight to covers.
Length ball around off, Vihari shoulders arms to it.
A length ball angling across Vihari, left alone.
Length ball around off, Rahane blocks it out solidly.
A good length just outside off, Rahane is not interested in playing that.
Fuller length outside off, Rahane comes forward and leaves.
Length ball around off, played straight towards mid on.
Fullish ball around off, Rahane trods forward and blocks it.
Josh Hazlewood is back on. 6-1-17-0 are his numbers so far.
Short of a length outside off, Rahane leaves it alone.
Length ball around off, blocked solidly by Vihari.
Length ball around middle, tucked it towards fine leg for a single.
A low full toss on the pads, Vihari misses his flick and they collect a leg bye.
Rahane is off the mark on the 17th ball. A bouncer down the leg side, Rahane pulls it down to fine leg for one.
A length ball around off, pushed towards covers.
Outside off, left alone.
Fullish delvery on the pads, Vihari flicks it in the gap at mid-wicket to collect a brace as the mid on fielder chases it.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Length ball on the stumps, tucked away on the leg side.
FOUR! Classy stuff this from Vihari. A fullish ball on the stumps, Vihari flicks this one towards mid-wicket boundary to collect four.
A length ball on the pads, Rahane looks to tuck but get hits on the pad and they take a leg bye as the ball goes towards the leg side.
Good length outside off, left alone by Rahane.
A maiden to begin from Starc. A very full ball around off and middle, Vihari pushes it back to the bowler.
Very full ball outside off, blocked.
Good leave! This one is fuller and just outside off, Vihar lets it go again. The ball tails back in but does so after going past the stick.
In the channel again, Vihari lets it go.
Around off on a length, kept out.
In the channel outside off to begin, Vihari lets it go to the keeper.
Finally, Cummins gets the break. Here's Mitchell Starc. 4-2-14-1 from him so far.
Good drive again but no run again. Full and around off, driven to the left of the man at mid off who doesn't let it go past him.
Outside off, left alone.

Huge appeal but it is turned down! No review from Australia as Paine suggests it would go over the stumps. A length ball around off, it sharply comes back in and beats the bat of Rahane. He is struck high on the pad and the Aussies appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Just outside off on a good length, Rahane covers his stumps and allows it to go to the keeper.
Edgy! Full and outside off, Vihari looks to drive but it goes off the outside edge through gully. Three taken before the fielder can chase it down.
Outside off on a length. Vihari shoulders arms.
Driven nicely but for nothing. Another maiden from Cummins. Full and outside off, Rahane drives it well but finds mid off.
Outside off on a length, left alone.
Gets behind the line of the ball this time to defned it on the off side.
Edged but doesn't carry, AGAIN! Fullish ball just outside off, Rahane this time looks to defend but gets an outside edge but the ball falls short of the man at third slip.
In the channel again, Rahane allows it to go to the keeper.
Fuller and outside off, Rahane lets it go to the keeper.
A maiden from Green. The last ball is short but outside off so Vihari lets it go again.
Wide outside off, easy leave for Vihari.
Shortish and around middle, tucked towards the leg side.
Shortish and around middle and leg, Vihari looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pad.
Length ball around off, blocked.
Fuller and around off and middle, flicked to mid on.
Vihari is off the mark with a good stroke! A fuller ball around off, he strokes it through mid off. Labuschagne chases it down with a slide near the long off fence. Three taken.
In the channel outside off to the new man. Vihari shoulders arms.
Hanuma Vihari is in now.

An intriguing first hour of play! It looked like two overnight Indian batters will see off the first hour comfortably but Gill fell for 45 trying to play an expansive drive to Cummins. And now, the wicket of Pujara means Australia will take the honors of winning the first hour. The Indians now need to stitch a good stand. Australia, on the other hand, will look to get a couple of more wickets quickly to put India further on the back foot.

OUT! CAUGHT! A stunner of a catch from Paine and Australia get the massive wicket of Pujara. It is that man Cummins again. Huge, huge wicket. Lovely bowling from Cummins again. It pitches just around off and it moves just a hint. Pujara looks to defend but gets an outside edge. The ball goes to the right side of Paine. It is in front of the first slip fielder but Paine dives to his right and the ball sticks in his hand. A superb take from the Aussie skipper as it would have fallen short of the slip fielder again. Credit to Cummins as well for steaming in, in this extended spell and he has got the reward for bowling in the right line and length.
Just outside off on a good length, Pujara covers his sticks and allows it to go to the keeper.
Full and outside off, Pujara this time leans and pushes it through the covers. Returns for a brace easily.
Length ball around off, blocked on the leg side.
Outside off on a good length. Left alone.
Full and around off, Rahane pushes it towards the cover region.
Length and around off, worked wide of the man at mid on for one.
In the channel outside off, Pujara covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
A bumper outside off, Pujara ducks.
Length ball around off, pushed towards point and a loud call for no.
Who will walk out now? Will it be skipper Rahane who will promote himself up the order? Yes, Rahane is in at 4.

OUT! TAKEN! Cummins finally gets his man. A lose shot from Gill and this time he runs out of his luck. He wanted to go after Cummins here but falls in the process. Lovely from Cummins. He deserves this wicket. Fuller and outside off, Gill looks to go for the big booming drive through the covers but he ends up nicking it behind. A simple chance for Paine behind the sticks. Paine will not make any mistake. Australia get the breakthrough they were after. A fine knock from Gill but he would feel he has thrown away a top start.
Down the leg side, Pujara looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball hits his pad and goes to fine leg for a leg bye.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, driven nicely by Pujara but straight to the cover fielder.
On the pads, flicked to deep square leg for one.
Good length and around off, blocked.

Edged but short. The Indians are riding their luck at the moment. A length ball just outside off, Pujara pokes at it with hard hands. The ball takes the outside edge but falls short of the man at first slip.

Was that a chance? A fuller ball on middle and leg, Pujara flicks it uppishly. The ball goes to the left of the leg gully fielder who dives to his left but it goes away from him. Two taken before fine leg can get around.
Landed outside off on a shortish length. Pujara makes another leave.
Length ball just outside off, moves away a touch as Pujara shoulders arms.
Full and on middle, pushed towards mid on.
A short ball to begin from Green. It is outside off, easy for Pujara to get out of the way.
Cameron Green to bowl now. No Starc yet.
A solid back foot block to the last ball of the over from Gill.
Another short ball, punched towards cover for nothing.
Back of a length and around off, defended towards the cover fielder this time.
Shortish and just around off, pushed towards the man at point off the back foot.
Sharp bumper around off, Gill drops his hands and allows it to go to the keeper.

EDGY FOUR! Credit to Gill for playing with soft hands though. Length ball around off, Gill looks to defend but gets an outside edge that goes between second slip and gully and into the third man fence. Frustrating for the Aussies.
Fullish ball around off, Pujara dabs it softly towards gully.
Length ball outside off, Pujara lets it be.
A good length ball on middle, Pujara looks to defend but gets hit high on the pads.
Shortish length ball around off, Pujara blocks this out on the on side.
In the channel outside off, an easy leave for Pujara.
Full and just wide outside off, Pujara lets it be.
Back of a length and around off, solidly blocked off the back foot by Gill.
Short and wide outside off, punched towards the man at backward point.
Play and a miss! Goes for the expansive drive through the covers as Cummins bowls this full and wide. Makes no connection does Gill.
Super shot but for no runs! A fullish ball around off, Gill hits it hard and straight back to the bowler. Cummins gets down quickly to stop the ball.
A bumper on middle, Gill sits under it.
Length ball just outside off, poked towards the man at gully.
What a ripper to end! How did that miss the bat? A length ball around off, comes back in a touch as Pujara pokes at it but is beaten for inside edge.
Full delivery on middle, Pujara flicks it to mid-wicket again.
Back of a length on middle, Pujara flicks it to mid-wicket.
Length delivery outside off, Pujara offers no shot to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Gill flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Good length delivery on off, Gill defends it off the back foot.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Pujara looks to defend but misses it.
Back of a length on middle, Pujara keeps it out.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Pujara looks to defend but misses it due to the seam movement on this one.
Length delivery on middle, Pujara flicks it through square leg for a couple.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara leaves it alone.
Bouncer on middle, Pujara does well to duck under it.
Similar ball around off, Gill is solid in his defense.
A fullish length just around off, blocked solidly by Gill.
Drifting down the pads, Pujara tucks this away towards square leg and they run 3.
A length ball around middle, Pujara plays it down towards mid- wicket.
A fullish ball outside off, Gill drives it handsomely through the covers and they run 3 before the fielder returns the ball.
FOUR! EDGY! A length ball around off, Gill gets an inside edge, the ball misses the stumps and also Paine to run away towards the fiine leg boundary.
Fullish ball around off, played towards covers by Pujara.
Length ball around off, defended solidly.
A short bumper on the body, Pujara ducks under it.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Just short! A length ball outside off, Pujara gets the edge, but the ball doesn't carry to first slip.
Length ball around off, Pujara block this out.
A length ball around off, defended solidly.
Length ball way outside off, Gill lets it be.
FOUR! LOVELY SHOT! A fullish ball around middle, Gill flicks this one through mid- wicket to get a boundary.

Dropped! Paine puts down a chance. A length ball around off, it comes back in sharply as Gill plays at it away from his body. He gets an inside edge. The ball goes to the left of the keeper but Paine fails to hold on.
A length ball outside off, left alone.
Length ball on middle, Gill misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.
Who will bowl from the other end? Josh Hazlewood it is.
A length ball around off defended solidly.
A good length ball outside off, left alone.
Length ball around off, defended towards short leg.
Length ball on the stumps, defended solidly by Pujara.
Good length ball outside off, guided down to gully.

Huge appeal but it has been turned down! Action on the first ball of Day 2. A good length ball just around off, it moves away just a touch as it goes past Pujara's poke. It goes behind and Paine takes the catch and appeals. The umpire turns down. Paine though is confident and he takes the appeal upstairs. Replays roll in and Hot Spot shows nothing. RTS has a little murmur but it is not enough for the TV umpire to overturn the onfield call. Pujara stays and Australia lose the review. What a start though.

Hello and welcome to Day 2 of the Boxing Day Test. On Day 1, it was all about the Indian bowlers as they bundled the Aussies to a low score. They lost Agarwal in the very first over but after that Gill along with Pujara managed to stay out in the middle. The duo will now walk out with the intent of batting long. The Aussies, on the other hand, have to be on the money. They will look to strike early in the first session of the day. An exciting day's play is coming our way. There is a forecast of some rain but let's hope we don't have any such interruptions. Stay tuned.
... Day 2, Session 1 ...

Right! That's all from the action on Day 1. It is India who end on top but on Day 2, their batters have to continue doing the good work. The Aussie quicks and Lyon won't be giving away runs that easily. So, it promises to be another intriguing day of Test cricket. That' all for now. Join us for Day 2 on 27th December 2020 at 1030 local (2330 GMT Previous Day). We will look for your company. Until then, take care!

India had to negotiate a testing phase and the Aussie quicks were in the rhythm straightaway. Starc removed Agarwal in the very first over and he along with Cummins beat the outside edge multiple times but couldn't induce the edge as Gill and Pujara made sure Indians did not lose another wicket. On the way to his unbeaten 28, Gill has played a few delightful strokes already.

The bowling from India was right on the money! Bumrah led the attack with 4-fer and Siraj, the debutant who replaced Shami too did really well. Ashwin was superb in his spell as he got better of Smith again and got two more. Umesh was the only one who didn't have a wicket to his name as others around him did the job for the team.

Paine opted to bat first after winning the toss and the decision didn't turn a good one for him and Australia. They lost Burns early. Wade played a few fine strokes but fell. Head and Labuschagne combined to add 86 between them but once the stand was broken, Australia lost the way completely and none of their batters could stop the Indian bowlers.

What an amazing Day 1 of the Boxing Day Test! India with the upper hand one would believe. After losing the toss, their bowlers weaved magic from start. Bumrah was the chief tormentor as he got 4 wickets and helped India bundle out Australia for a low total. And then, after losing Agarwal early, Gill and Pujara have done well to see off the remaining threat!
A fullish ball around off, Gill comes on the front foot and blocks it solidly. With this solid block, it is Stumps on Day 1.
Hesitation again but safe again. A length ball around off and middle, Gill pushes it wide of the man at mid on and calls for a single. He takes a few step forward but Pujara sends him back.
Shortish and just outside off, pushed towards point by Gill. Last 2 balls coming up.
Length ball outside off, easy leave this time.
Risky leave! A length ball, this one is just outside off, Gill covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper. It wasn't too far away from the off pole.

Confusion but safe in the end. A length ball around off, Pujara pushes it towards point and goes for a run. Gill sends him back. The fielder has a shy but he misses. There is no one to do back up as the ball goes towards deep mid-wicket and they eventually get the single.
Tossed up and around off, Gill comes on the front foot to block.
Floated full and around off, pushed towards mid off.
On off, watchfully defended.
FOUR! Drilled! Full and around off, Gill comes down the track and creams it through mid off and bags another boundary.
Floated around off, Gill comes on the front foot to defend.
Full and just outside off to begin, Gill drives it through covers and gets a brace.
Full and around off, kept out.
Tight first over from Hazlewood. Shortish and around off, Pujara stays back to push it towards the cover region. Josh will have to bowl this one again as the TV umpire has called it a no ball.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards mid on.
Beaten! A good length ball outside off stump, Pujara looks to play at it but gets beaten. That was a trademark Hazlewood delivery right in the corridor of uncertainty.
Fuller length ball on the pads, Pujara misses the flick and gets hit on the pads. A slight appeal from the Australian players but nothing from the umpire.
A length ball around off, Pujara taps it towards covers and runs but goes back after his partner says no.
Length ball down the leg side, Pujara lets it be.
Josh Hazlewood to bowl now. Wade has gone off the field. Looked in some trouble while he tried to stop the ball near the fence.
Shortish and around off, tapped towards point for a single.
A big bumper which goes well over Pujara. He ducks under it.
Lovely timing! A fuller length ball on the stumps, Giill drives it gloriously past mid off to take 3 more runs as Wade from mid off chases and keeps the ball in play.
Shortish ball on middle, defended straight back by Gill.
Length ball outside off, guides it to the right of gully where Green stops it.
Length ball around off, worked on the leg side for a run.

FOUR! Another boundary for Gill. Starc runs in and dishes the full ball on the pads. The Indian batters love it there. Gill flicks it to the right side of the mant at fine leg. The fielder tries to cut it off but fails to do so.
Very full and around off, kept out.

FOUR! TAKE THAT! Starc bangs it short and it is on middle, Gill rocks back and powerfully pulls it over mid-wicket for a boundary. Wanted to leave it alone at first but went with the shot and fetched a boundary for himself.
Back of a length and around off, pushed towards point.
Goes wide outside off, Gill shoulders arms.
Back of a length ball around off, Gill hangs his bat in defense but the ball shapes away to beat the outside edge.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Pujara is up and running with a fine shot. A fuller ball around middle, Pujara waits for the ball to come closer to him and then he just punches the drive through mid on.
Fuller and around off, worked on the leg side.
This time Pujara goes on the back foot to block it out nicely.
This one comes back in after pitching around middle. Pujara looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pad.
Fuller and around off, pushed to mid on.
Full and wide, Gill thinks to play the booming drive through the off side but opts against it at the last second.
WOW! What a ripper! You just can't play these. Unplayable delivery. This one is pitched around off on a good length, it pitches and then shapes away a touch to beat the poke of Gill.
Nicely done! A length ball just around off, Gill waits for the ball and then taps it wide of the gully fielder. Two taken before backward point can get to the ball.
Short and wide outside off, pushed towards point.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Crunched! Fine shot from Gill again. Short and wide outside off. Gill pounces on the width outside off and nails it through point for a boundary.

Put down! Gill gets a life. Cummins runs in and bowls this full and around off, Gill looks to flick but gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes to Labuschagne at third slip. It is to his right. He gets both his hands but fails to hold onto it.
Back of a length and around off, blocked off the back foot.

FOUR! Gill is off the mark in style! That is some stroke to get off the mark in Test cricket. A fuller ball around off, Gill drives it through mid off. The fielder gives it a chase but fails to cut if off. This should calm Gill's nerves out in the middle.
Shortish and around off, poked towards the gully fielder.
Absolute beauty! Nothing much Gill can do about it. A length delivery around off, the batter has to play at it. Gill does that but is beaten.
Length ball around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Starc goes past the bat again. Consecutive maidens for him. Just outside off on a good length, Pujara has to play at it. He does that off the back foot but is beaten.
Length and outside off, kept out.
Shortish and just outside off, Pujara hides his bat and allows the ball to go to the keeper.
Fullish and around off, a solid block from Pujara this time.
Pujara is beaten now! A length ball just outside off, shapes away as Pujara pokes at it.
Length and around off, Pujara forces it on the off side.
A maiden from Cummins as on the last ball, Gill gets behind the line to keep it out.
Beaten again! Gill feels for it again as this one is full and outside off. Once again Gill makes no connection as the ball goes past the outside edge.
Beaten! Lovely stuff from Cummins. This one pitches on a good length and then kicks off as Gill pokes at it to get beaten.
Another lovely delivery. This one pitches around off and jags back in. Gill looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit high on the pad.
A ripper from Cummins now. A length ball just outside off, Gill pokes at it but makes no connection.
Wide outside off, Gill shoulders arms.
Who will walk out to bat now? Cheteshwar Pujara it is. Pat Cummins will bowl from the other end for Australia.

OUT! LBW! Umpire's call on hitting the wickets. Starc has struck early and Agarwal fails again. Lovely stuff from Starc and he is pumped up. A good length ball just around off, comes back in just a touch as Agarwal looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pad. They appeal and the finger is raised. Agarwal is not too sure if he has got any bat but he goes for the review. Replays roll in and it shows that the ball has hit the pad first. Ball Tracker shows it to be umpire's call on hitting the wickets. So, Agarwal has to go. India keep their review though but a horrid start again for India.

Review time! Agarwal has been given out LBW but after having a word with his debutant partner at the other end, Agarwal signals the 'T' at the very last second. Let's see what the replays have got to show? It has hit the pad first. And the Ball Tracker shows umpire's call on hitting the wicket.
In the channel outside off, Agarwal doesn't flirt with it.
Good length and around off, Agarwal is right behind the line of the ball to block.
Lovely delivery again. A yorker around off, Agarwal did really well to get his foot out of the way and then block it out.

Huge appeal for LBW but the umpire turns it down. Looks like there was some bat and height looks to be an issue too. They don't take the review. Good length ball just outside off, Agarwal looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pad. They all go up in a loud appeal but nothing from the umpire. Replays roll in and it shows a big inside edge.
Starc is right on the money! A length ball around off and middle, a touch of inward movement but Agarwal does really well to block it off his front foot.

We are back! The Australian players have made their way out in the middle. Mayank Agarwal has a new partner with him in debutant Shubhman Gill. The 21-year-old has got a tough ask in front of him. Mitchell Starc with the ball first up for Australia. Here we go...

Right! 70 is what India need to level the series. The fact that the conditions are pretty good to bat, they should chase it down easily. However, they will remember their score of last match's second innings and would not want to get carried away. Australia, if they can strike early, can put the visitors under some pressure. Join us for India's 2nd innings in a short while.

The man who got India the breakthrough in the morning, Jasprit Bumrah is caught for a quick chat. Bumrah says that he is really happy with their performance with the ball. Tells that they had decided not to complain about having one bowler short. Adds that they decided to help the new members coming in the team. On him being the leader of the attack, Bumrah says that they had decided to help each other. On his performance from the last 2 games, Bumrah says that he doesn't look at the stats because that will put unnecessary pressure on him and would rather focus on doing the basics correct.

The day started with the two Aussie overnight batters continuing their fight. They nearly managed to remain unscathed in the first hour of the morning before a snorter from Bumrah got the better of Cummins. Green continued the battle along with Starc but was removed eventually by Siraj on 45 as he tried to play a pull shot. The other batters resisted a bit before Ashwin removed Hazlewood in the last over of the extended first session. The bowlers didn't put themselves under any sort of pressure and just kept bowling good lines and lengths and they were sure about the rewards which eventually came their way. In spite of having one man short, they worked well to bundle out the Aussies.

Another session to India and they inch closer to the victory. They had to work hard in this session as Green and Cummins resisted well. However, once the stand got broken, it was only about how long they can survive. They did manage to do it for a decent amount of period but they needed runs. They got just 68 in this extended morning session of Day 4 which means India need 70.

OUT! TIMBER! Ashwin with the success. A flat ball around middle and leg, Hazlewood thinks that it will spin away way too much as he shoulders arms. To his dismay, the ball clips the off pole and takes the bails along with it. Australia are bowled out for 200. India need 70 to level the series.
Final over before the Lunch break coming up.
Yorker on middle, Starc digs it out.
Outside off on a length, left alone.
Short on middle, Starc ducks under it.
Shorter around off, Starc sways away from it.
A length ball around of, poked past gully towards third man for a single. 200 up for Australia now and they lead by 69 now.
Fuller and outside off, pushed to point.
Change of ends for Jasprit Bumrah.

LBW appeal taken upstairs. Has Ashwin got his man? The umpire thinks otherwise but the Indians go for the review. There is no bat, confirmed by Hot Spot. Nothing on RTS either. Time for the Ball Tracker. Umpire's call on hitting the wickets.

NOT OUT! Umpire's call on hitting the wickets. Starc survives a calls that could've gone against him. Flighted ball on the pads, Starc looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get his on the pads. The Indians put in a loud appeal but it is turned down. Rahane goes for the review. Hot Spot and RTS confirm no bat. Ball Tracker shows it would just clip the leg pole. So, Starc stays to continue the battle. India keep their review.
Tossed up outside off, turns way as Starc watches it go to the keeper.
Short and on middle, Starc pulls it wide of the man at fine leg for a couple.
On off, a solid front foot defense this time.
Shortish and just outside off, pushed towards point.
Flatter and around middle, Starc tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Ashwin is back on. 36-6-69-1 from him so far.
Slower fuller one around off, Hazlewood reads it well and pushes it towards cover.
A well-directed bumper. Hazlewood does well to move out of the way.
Length ball angled in, Starc tucks it through square leg for a single.
Another one outside off, Starc lets it go.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Length ball around middle, Starc looks to work it on the leg side but gets a leading edge towards gully.
Good bouncer to end the over! Starc does well to get away from the firing line.
Full and outside off, stroked through covers for a brace.
A bumper now! Josh sits under it.
Beaten! Length ball outside off, angles away and beats the outside edge of Starc.
Length ball on middle, defended on the back foot.
Short on leg, tucks this one towards fine leg for a single.
Bouncer around off, Josh allows it to go to the keeper by dropping his hands.
A mixture of short and length ball here by Siraj. A length ball just around off, misses the edge.
Almost! A shorter on middle, Hazlewood looks to fend, but misses and the ball goes to Pant.
Follows the short ball with a length ball around off, beating Hazlewood's defence.
Short on middle again, Hazlewood looks to play the upper cut but misses.
Short ball on middle, kept out.
Length ball around off, Hazlewood looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards square leg. They cross.
Goes for the yorker but ends up bowling a full toss. Starc mistimes it towards short fine leg.
Baged short but down the leg side. Josh ducks under.
Yorker this time! Starc does well to flick it down to fine leg for a run.
Short ball on middle, Starc sits under it.
A bumper straightaway. Hazlewood fends it towards short fine leg for one.
With just 1 wicket left, the lunch has been extended by 30 minutes. Also, here's Bumrah again. Can he knock the last man out quickly?
Swing and a miss! Short ball on middle, Starc goes for the pull but makes no connection. End of a successful over from Siraj.

FIVE RUNS! Needless from Siraj. A shortish ball around middle, Josh tucks it towards the leg side and goes for a quick single. Siraj quickly gets to the ball and has a needless shy at the non-striker's end. He misses and there is no one doing the back up and the ball races away to the long off fence.
Josh Hazlewood in at no 11.

OUT! CAUGHT! Siraj gets another one. Australia are 9 down. The effort ball from Siraj. He bangs it short and on middle and leg, Lyon goes for the pull but ends up getting a bit of gloves to the left of the keeper. Pant moves that way and takes the catch. They appeal and once again the finger has gone up.  Lyon knows he has hit it. He keeps walking. Wicket number 3 for Siraj. Australia leading by 54 runs.
Length on middle, Lyon looks to tuck but misses.
Fuller ball on middle, driven to mid on.
Shorter around middle, tucked towards leg gully.

NOT OUT! Technology saves Starc. Flat ball around off, Starc looks to flick but misses. The ball hits his pad and goes to first slip. Rahane takes the catch and they appeal. The finger is raised. And Starc takes the DRS straightaway. Replays roll in. It shows that his bat has hit his shoes which is detected by the Hot Spot. The umpire checks the LBW call as well. Ball Tracker shows missing the stumps.
Starc has been given out! He has asked for the review. Let's see if the technology can save him.
Tossed up and around off, Starc is on the front foot to block.
Misfield and two! Flat and around middle, Starc flicks it to the left of the mid-wicket fielder who misfields and allows two.
Just short. Full and on middle, Starc flicks it uppishly. It is just short of the man at mid-wicket.
Play and a miss! Flat and wide outside off, Starc looks to punch but misses.
Tossed up on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and on middle, flicked down to fine leg for a run.
Bumper just around off, Starc lets it go to Pant.
Good length and around off, poked towards point.
Fuller and on the pads, Lyon looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball goes wide of the man at short fine leg and they take a leg bye.
This one is on middle and leg, Lyon ducks under it.
A bumper around off, Lyon sways away from the line.
On off, kept out off the back foot this time.
Outside off, left alone.
Beaten! Superb ball from Ashwin. This one pitches around leg and then goes away as Starc looks to defend but is beaten.
Tossed up outside off, Lyon goes for the drive but gets a thick outside edge that goes wide of the man at point. They take a run. The lead is now 50.
Fuller and around middle, Lyon tucks it towards short fine leg.
Flat and around off, pushed back to Ashwin.
Almost gets him! A fuller length ball around off, Starc looks to play at it, but misses and the ball goes through to Pant.
Short this time to Starc but outside off, Starc leaves it alone.
Short around middle, Lyon pulls this one towards fine leg for a single.
Fuller length on middle, flicked away towards mid on.
Similar ball, similar shot from Lyon but straight to the fielder.
Fuller ball outside off, Lyon drives it towards covers.
On the pads on a fullish length, Starc is blocking it again.
Tossed up full and around middle, Starc blocks.
Lyon is off the mark now. This is tossed up nicely. Lyon goes back and pokes it to gully for one.
On off, driven to long off for one.
Slower through the air and on middle, defended.
Flatter and around middle, pushed to mid on.
Nathan Lyon in at number 10. How long can he survive ?

OUT! TAKEN! Green falls. The debutant has got the job done for India here. India one step closer to the win. A shortish ball around middle, Green looks to pull. However, it goes off the higher part of his bat and goes to Jadeja at mid-wicket. He seems to have lost it for a moment but does well to catch over his head. A fighting knock from Green comes to an end. Australia lead by 46 runs.
Fuller and around off, kept out.
FOUR! SHOT! FIne shot! Fuller and around middle, Green drills it to the right of the man at mid on. He gives it a chase but comes second.
Wide outside off, left alone.
KL Rahul, the substitute with a fine stop. Fuller and around off, Starc drills it towards mid on. Rahul runs to his left and dives to stop. Just a run. Saves 3.
Appeal but nothing from the umpire. Fuller and on middle and leg, Starc looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. An appeal but turned down.
Flatter and just outside off, pushed to the right of the man at mid off. Now, Siraj will have a go at Starc in the next over.
Tossed up and around off, watchfully blocked.
Fuller and around middle, flicked down to deep square leg for one.
On off, kept out.
Tossed up outside off, pushed to mid off this time.
Full and around off, blocked back to the bowler.
Jadeja is on now! His figures so far are 12-5-25-2.
A dot on the last ball. So, Starc will be back on strike. Good from Siraj. He bends his back and bangs it short. Green ducks under it.
Fuller around off, defended towards covers.

Close! A fuller ball outside off, Green drives it towards mid off and starts to run, but then sends Starc back, who just makes it at the non striker's end as the mid off fielder has a shy at the stumps.
Full ball on middle, Green does well to block it.
Run out appeal taken upstairs. Has Starc got himself back in time? Yes, he has.

NOT OUT! Starc has done well there. A length ball around off, Green pushes it back to the bowler. Siraj in his followthrough gets his hands to it as the ball goes to hit the stumps. They appeal. The third umpire has been called for. Replays show Starc has got himself in.
Full and way outside off, Green leaves it alone.
Mohammed Siraj is back on. 14.3-2-24-1 from him so far.
Two now and the lead goes to 40. Full and on middle, Starc flicks it through mid-wicket and scampers back for the second.
On off, kept out.
Tossed up and around middle, again kept out by Starc.
Loopy on middle, solid front foot block.
Floated outside off, left alone.
Tossed up and around middle, pushed back to the bowler.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off, Green slashes it through backward point and finds the fence. Good way to end the over.
Fuller and around off, blocked.
FOUR LEG BYES! Bumrah misses his line and bowls it on the pad. Green looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball goes to the fine leg fence past the diving keeper.
Fullish and just outside off, Green is solid in defense.
Length and around off, kept out.
Outside off, left alone.
A single and Green will keep the strike. Shortish and around off, played to long on for a run. Should've had got the long on fielder inside the ring.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Fuller and around off, kept out.
Short and outside off, poked towards mid off.
Flatter and outside off, played back to the bowler.
Short and outside off, pushed to mid on.
Bumrah goes for the yorker but Green flicks it nicely. It is wide of the man at fine leg. Before he can come around, they take three.
Fuller and around middle, Green flicks well but finds mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.
Banged short to Green, this goes down the leg side as Green ducks.
Fullish and outside off, pushed to mid off.
Good length and around off, poked towards point.
Tossed up and outside off, Starc punches it well but hits it straight at the man at silly point.
The quicker one on the pads, Starc looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Outside off, left alone.
Loopy ball around off, blocked out.
On off, blocked.
Tossed up and outside off, left alone.

Another bumper! This time to the new man. Starc has no clue how to deal with it. Tries to duck but is late in doing so. The ball takes the top edge and goes to fine leg. The fielder there does well to stop the ball. They check with the third umpire and it is a good save. End of a superb over from Bumrah.

Drinks! The first hour has all been about patience for both the teams. Australia almost managed to go unscathed but then Bumrah came up with unplayable ball to Cummins and now India have an opening. How long the tail will survive?  Mitchell Starc is the new batsman in at number 9.

OUT! TAKEN! Bumrah with a snorter and Cummins has no answers to that. After bowling length deliveries outside off, this time Bumrah bends his back and bowls a short ball around middle and leg. Cummins is caught in an awkward position as he hops and tries to fend it off. All he does is lobs the ball off the gloves to Agarwal at second slip. A gritty knock from Cummins but that was an unplayable ball from Bumrah.
Outside off on a good length. Left alone.
Full and around middle, flicked wide of the man at mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and around off, kept out.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Quick single! Floated around off, it is pushed towards mid off and they take a quick run.
Flatter and around middle and leg, pushed to mid on.
FOUR! First boundary of the day. Short and wide outside off, Green slashes it through point for a boundary.
On middle, played back to the bowler.
Short and wide, Cummins punches it wide but Siraj dives to his right at covers to keep it for a run. 150 is up for the Aussies and the lead is 19.
Flatter and around middle, kept out.
A solid defense this time from Green off the front foot. A maiden.
Very full and around off, blocked towards mid on.
Outside off, left alone.
Appeal for LBW but nothing doing. A length ball around off, this one came back in after pitching. Green looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pad. An appeal but turned down.
Another fuller one outside off, shapes away further after going past the batter.
A fullish ball outside off to begin, Green lets it be.
The second new ball is due now! Will Rahane go for it straightaway? Yes, they have gone for it. So, Bumrah is back too.
On middle, Cummins is solid in defense again.
Tossed up and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Another loopy ball around middle, Cummins taps it onto the pitch.
Looped ball and on middle, kept out.
Loopy ball on the legs, Pat pads it away.
A quick single as Green pushes it to mid on. The single brings up 50-run stand between the two.
Another leave as Jadeja bowls it wide outside off.
Floated outside off, left alone.
Tossed up and around off, Cummins comes on the front foot to block.
Floated around off, blocked.
On middle, defended back to Jadeja again.
Flat and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Loopy ball around off, a solid front foot defense. It was the carrom ball but Green read it well.
Green once again uses his feet. This time he covers the spin and defends.
On middle, pushed wide of the leg gully fielder for a single.
Green comes down the track and pushes it down to long off for one.
Flat and around off, kept out.
Shortish and around off, punched through covers for brace.
Excellent stop at gully. Gill is the man. Shortish and just outside off, Cummins cuts but Gill dives to his left to save runs.
Appeal for LBW, a loud one from Jadeja but the umpire is unmoved. This is the slider from Jadeja. It pitches on middle and leg and Cummins misses his flick to get hit on the pad.
Shortish and around middle, pushed to mid on.
Flatter around off, turned towards mid-wicket.
Fuller this time, defended towards the bowler.
Flatter around off, blocked by Pat.

Time for Ravindra Jadeja to roll his arms now. The second new ball is due after 4 overs. So, maybe Rahane wants to take it quickly. Can Jadeja provide a breakthrough to the Indians with this old ball?
Floated around off, Green comes down and defends.
Tossed up around middle, blocked.
Floated around middle, tucked towards square leg for single.

NOT OUT! Missing leg and going over too. India lose a review. A quicker one around middle and leg, Cummins pads it away and the Indians appeal but not out says the umpire. Ashwin thinks he has got his man. Rahane thinks, thinks and just thinks. And then at the last moment, takes the review. Doesn't help India as the Ball Tracker shows it is missing the leg pole.
Review time! India have gone for a review against Cummins. Rahane went for it almost at the end of the timer! Let's see what the repalys have to show.
Flat and around off, blocked.
On off, defended.
Shortish around middle, tucked towards mid-wicket.
Bouncer on middle, Green ducks under it. Someone may have told Siraj that Green was standing outside the crease.
Good length, blocked solidly.
Fuller around off, driven to mid off.
On a good length, defended solidly.
Length ball around off, blocked.

Huge appeal from Ashwin but turned down. Pant tells Ashwin that it won't hit the stumps. No review from the Indians. This is again tossed up and is bowled on middle and leg, Cummins pads it away again as Ashwin appeals but nothing from the umpire. Replay later rolled in and it showed it would've gone over the timbers and it would've missed it by some margin.
Tossed up and around off, blocked off the front foot.
Loopy outside off, left alone.
Floated on the pads, Cummins pads it away.
Good running! Floated outside off, Cummins stays back and then guides it towards third man. They take two.
Tossed up and around middle, tucked on the leg side.
Good length and around off, kept out by Green. Decent first over from Siraj.
Good leave! This one comes in with the angle from outside off as Green shoulders arms.
Another one wide outside off, Green makes another leave.
Outside off on a good length, left alone.
Fuller and wide outside off, driven to the left of the cover fielder for one.
Good length and around off, pushed towards point.
First change of the morning. Time for Mohammed Siraj to have a go. 12.3-1-23-1 are his figures so far.
Turn and bounce there. This one pitches around off and then turns in and bounces extra. Cummins goes back and fends it off the inner half through leg gully for one.
Tossed up outside off, Pat looks to defend but the ball takes a thick outside edge and goes towards gully.
This time he comes down the track and pushes it down to long on for one.
Tossed up and around off, Green comes down the track and flicks but finds mid-wicket.
Tossed up and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Floated on middle, kept out.
Fuller and around off, pushed to mid off.
Wide outside off, Cummins shoulders arms.
Banged short this time, Cummins sits under it. First bouncer of the morning.
Landed on a length and on middle, worked down to fine leg for one.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Fuller and around off, Green is solid in defense.
Fuller and around middle, turned towards short fine leg for nothing by Cummins.
Tossed up and around off, Cummins blocks. It looked like he wanted to go over the top for a moment but opted against it at the end. Ashwin gave the ball a lot of loop and slowed it down too.
Shortish and around middle, kept out off the back foot.
Quicker one on the pads, tucked on the leg side.
Flatter and around off, pushed towards point.
Full and around middle, pushed down to long on for one.
A maiden from Bumrah now. This is once again shortish in length and around middle, Cummins blocks it out.
Back of a length ball around off, Pat gets on top of the bounce to block.
Another length ball, tucked towards square leg.
Good length and around middle, worked on the leg side.

Edged but short! Lovely from Bumrah. After bowling the first ball on the stumps, Bumrah bowls this one just outside off on a good length. Cummins pokes at it without moving his feet. An outside edge is induced but the ball doesn't carry to Pujara at first slip.
Fuller and around off, Cummins keeps it out.
Tossed up and on middle, this time Green lunges ahead to defend. A maiden from Ashwin.
Slower through the air and a bit shortish in length. Green is on his back foot to block.
Fuller and around off, Green blocks again.
Floated outside off, easily defended.
Flatter and just outside off, Green stays back to defend.
Tossed up and just outside off, turning in, Green goes back and blocks.
Will it be spin from the other end? Yes! Here's Ravichandran Ashwin.
A single on the last ball. Another length ball around off, Green looks to defend but it takes the inner half and goes towards square leg for a run.
Solid again from Green. Another length ball around off from Bumrah. Green moves across to the off side and then blocks.
Around off on a length, Green defends it out.
Good length and around off, a solid front foot defense from Green.
Down the leg side, Green looks to flick but misses.

Runs straightaway! A length ball around off from Bumrah to begin, Green pushes it to the right of the fielder at point and they go for a quick single. He has a shy at the non-striker's end but he misses. The Aussies get one more in the form of overthrows as there is no one to back it up.

We are ready to start Day 4. The Indian players take the field following the two umpires. Cameron Green and Pat Cummins make their way out to the middle as well. The duo managed to frustrate the Indians in the final hour of Day 3 as they batted over 100 deliveries. That's what will be their aim once again. However, they will need to keep scoring runs as well. Jasprit Bumrah has got the ball first up. He would look to provide the early breakthrough to the Indians. All in readiness. Here we go...

Rishabh Pant is caught for a quick chat. On the discussion at the end of Day 3, Pant says that Rahane said that they need to concentrate and keep it simple and bowl good lines. Tells that he has no idea about Yadav's injury and he needs to ask the same to the physio. On him missing the first Test, Pant says that it's part and parcel of the game. Says he has been training hard and once he gets the chance, he looks to help the team do good. On keeping in Australia, Pant says that he is adjusting with respect to bounce. Tells that key on these wickets is to give yourself a bit of space when keeping against the likes of Ashwin and Jadeja. On his banter with Wade, Pant says that he enjoys every bit of it. Adds that Wade wanted to get going with some sort of discussion to concentrate but adds he didn't want to let him do that.

Hello and welcome to Day 4 of the Boxing Day Test between Australia and India. The game is poised well and truly in the favour of the Indian side and Rahane's men would look to seal the deal in the first session itself. They would not want the pair of Cummins and Green to get settle again and frustrate them. Australia, on the other hand, knows they are in big trouble and would want these two to continue batting as long as possible. Will they be able to do so or will Bumrah and others roll them over? We will get all the answers once the action resumes. Stay tuned.
... Day 4, Session 1 ...

So, that ends another enthralling day's play! India will feel they are well on top of this match. They just need 4 wickets to bundle the Aussies and that they would look to do in the first session of Day 4. Australia, on the other hand, would want these two to bat long. Will they be able to do so? We will find out all these things on Day 4. The action will begin at 1030 local (2330 GMT Previous Day). Join us for that. For now, it is goodbye from our end.

Indian skipper, Ajinkya Rahane, is caught for a quick chat. Rahane says that the bowlers came out strong and bowled tight lines. Says it was unfortunate to miss out Yadav. Adds that captaincy is all about backing the instincts. Credits the bowlers for bowling on right lines and lengths. On his century, Rahane says that getting to a hundred while captaining the side is always special. Feels his century at Lord's is his best knock. On him patting Jadeja after getting run out, Rahane says that he told him to not think about the run out and carry on his innings. On asked if the same was said to him by skipper Kohli in the first Test, Rahane tells that he got out quickly after Kohli's wicket and adds Kohli told him it is okay.

The second session saw India get Burns early and then Wade and Labuschagne put on a fight. Ashwin removed Labuschagne to break the stand and then along with Smith, Wade fought hard to stay in the middle in the entire second session. However, the final session of the day turned things around quickly for the visitors as they took control of the game with quick wickets.

The day started with India losing their 5 wickets for just 32 runs but they extended their lead to 131. The collapse happened after Rahane got run out trying to steal a run for Jadeja so that he gets to his half ton. Jadeja eventually got there but soon joined Rahane in the pavilion after a barrage of short balls from Starc troubled him. The Aussies then finished the Indian innings quickly with Starc and Lyon getting 3 each.

Once again it was Bumrah who opened the floodgates for the Indians with the wicket of Smith. Jadeja then got the ball and struck twice quickly to force Australia on the back foot. Siraj too got a wicket. India would be disappointed a bit towards the end where they couldn't get past Green and Cummins and allowed the duo to bat over 100 balls.

What a session for India! Wade and Smith arrived in the middle and offered some resistance before Bumrah got the better of Smith as he bowled him around his legs. Wade then battled for a while with Head but once Wade fell, Australia crumbled as they lost three wickets for just 2 runs. Green and Cummins then batted really well to stitch a small partnership and make the Indian bowlers work hard. With this gritty stand, the duo made sure the Aussies have taken the lead now.
Slower through the air and around middle and leg, Cummins stays back to block. With that, it is STUMPS ON DAY 3.
Tossed up and around off and middle, turns in but Cummins blocks.
Green taking his time! He wants to make sure this is the last over.
Fuller and around middle, Green works it towards deep mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
FOUR! SHOT! Short and wide outside off, Green punches it past the man at mid off for a boundary. Australia take the lead. They are ahead by one.
Floated full and on middle, Green comes down the track and pushes it back to the bowler.
Length just around off, Cummins pushes this one towards point and runs, but returns back as his partner says a loud no.
Last over before Stumps coming up. Or maybe another one?
Shortish on the body, Green just tucks this one towards fine leg for a single.
Short time time but way down the leg side. Green lets it go.
Beaten! Fuller and outside off, Green goes for the big booming drive through the off side but is beaten all ends up.
Landed around off in a good length, a solid front foot block.
Full and wide outside off, left alone by Green.

Uppish but safe! Lovely from Ashwin. He tosses the last ball up and bowls it full on middle and leg, Cummins goes for the flick and does so uppishly towards mid-wicket. The ball though falls well short.
Fuller and around off, Cummins is on the front foot to defend.
Tossed up and outside off, forced towards cover region for one.
Shortish and just outside off, played towards the off side.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Play and a miss! Darted outside off, Green looks to cut but misses.
A maiden from Siraj. A length ball around middle and leg, Cummins pushes it towards mid on.
Back of a length and around middle, Pat stays back to block.
Good length and around off, Cummins defends it out solidly again.
Around off on a length, pushed back to the bowler.
Outside off on a length, Cummins drives but finds the cover fielder.
Bangs the first one short and it is aimed at the body. Cummins does well to get down.
Mohammed Siraj gets the ball again. Gets a piece of advice or two from Bumrah and Rahane.
Floated full on the pads, kept out but Green.
Tossed up around off, turns in but Green is up for the task as he blocks.
Pushes this fuller one gently to the right side of Ashwin for a run.
Tossed up and around off, watchfully blocked.
Short again, this time Green punches it wide of the cover fielder for one.
Flatter and outside off, punched through covers for one.
Bouncer to end the over, but down the leg, easily evaded by Green.
Lovely yorker from Bumrah. Green does well to block. Excellent from both bowler as well as the batter there.
Short again on middle, Green this time ducks under it.
Shortish around leg, tucked away towards deep square for a single.
Short time but down the leg, Cummins ducks under it.
Yorker on middle, Cummins does well to block it.
Looped up on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter and around middle, Cummins pushes it to mid on for one.
Floated around off, blocked by Cummins.
Beaten! Was there an edge there? A tossed up ball outside off, beats Cummins and Pant fails to collect it. Replays show there was a faint edge, so a chance put down by Pant.
Floated around off, pushed back.
Tossed up on middle and off, dabs it towards point.
Good length and around off, Green this time is solid in defense.
Bouncer again, this time Green ducks.
Ouch! A bumper and Green is late in getting down. He gets hit on the arm. Doesn't show any sort of pain there.
Lovely yorker! Green somehow manages to get bat on ball.
Shortish and around middle, Green gets on top of the bounce to block. Called no ball.
And again but this one is down the leg side. Green has no issues dealing with it.
A bouncer around off, Green ducks under it.
Floated full and on middle, Cummins comes forward and blocks.
Shortish again, kept out.
Around off on a shortish length. Cummins blocks.
Flatter and outside off, forced wide of the man at gully for one.
Loopy ball around off and middle, worked towards mid-wicket.
Floated around off, blocked.
Ashwin is back. 18-4-36-1 are his figures so far.
Attempted slower yorker ends up being a full toss. Cummins does well to block. Good variation by Bumrah to end the over.
Bumper around off, Cummins sits under it.
Length around off, blocked by Cummins.
Good length around off, defended solidly.
Fuller this time around off, played straight back to the bowler.
Length ball around middle, bunts it down towards mid on.
Jadeja slows this up and bowl it full around off, Green stays back to defend.
Shortish and around off, forced towards the cover fielder.
Flatter and around off, Green goes back to block.
FOUR! Hammered! A short ball on middle, Green rocks back and powers it over mid-wicket. One bounce and into the gence.
Shorter this time, punched to the left of cover for a single.
FOUR! Tossed up around off, Cummins goes over the top of mid off and gets a boundary. Some aggression now from Cummins.
Bouncer to finish the over, Green ducks under it.
Fuller this time, played softly towards covers.
Length around off, dabs it towards point.
Around off on a length, Green keeps it out.
Bouncer on middle, Green sits under it.
A length ball around off to begin, Green blocks.
Jasprit Bumrah is back. He has been impressive with figures of 13-2-32-1 so far.
Tossed up and around off, blocked out.
Floated outside off, driven well by Cummins but straight to the cover fielder.
Tossed up and around off, Green pushes it towards mid off and takes a quick single.
Quicker and around off, worked towards mid-wicket.
Full and on middle, worked towards square leg for one.
Floated around off, blocked by Pat.
Shot! Full and outside off, Cummins nails the drive through the covers. Ashwin chases it down and they take three.
Around off on a length, solid block from Pat.
Another good bumper! Cummins sits under it.
Fuller and around off, Cummins comes on the front foot to defend.
Good length and around off, Cummins pushes it towards point.
Sharp bouncer! It is just outside off, Green sways away.
Quicker one around middle, defened from within the crease. A maiden.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed back to Jadeja.
Flatter and around off, Green goes back to block.
A tossed up ball played back to the bowler.
Fuller ball defended of the front foot.
Flatter around off, defends it on the off side.
Similar ball, tucked away towards backward square leg.
Length ball around middle, flicked towards backward square leg.
Cummins defends it on the back foot.
Length on middle, tucked on the leg side for a run.
Fuller length outside off, left alone.

Huge appeal for LBW but turned down. That looked to be going down leg but Siraj was once again confident. But this time Rahane wasn't listening to him. Length ball angled in from outside off, Green looks to work it on the leg side but misses. They appeal but turned down. Replays show it to be missing leg by some distance.
Tossed up and outside off, left alone.
Flat and around off, kept out.
Loopy and around off, Cummins pushes it towards cover.
Shortish and around off, Pat stays back to defend.
Flatter around off, defended on the off side.
Flatter around off, driven towards covers and takes a quick run does Green. Called no ball as Jadeja has overstepped.
Around off, pushed towards mid off.
Length on middle, punched down the ground, the bowler gets a hand and diverts it towards mid off to give away the run.
Bumper now on middle and leg, Green ducks under it.
Length on middle, played with a straight bat.
A length ball on middle, flicked straight to mid-wicket.
Length on middle, played it down t on the on side.
Length ball around off, defended straight.
Full and around off, defened back to the bowler. Another successful over from Jadeja.
On middle, clipped to fine leg for a brace by Cummins to open his account.
Pat Cummins comes in to bat at number 8.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Paine has to go as RTS spots an edge. Paine is not pleased. He just cannot believe it. A tossed up delivery just outside off, it turns away and bounces extra as Paine looks to cut but misses. Pant collects and appeals along with the bowler. Not out says the umpire but Rahane goes for the review straightaway. The Hot Spot rolls in. Nothing on it. RTS detects the bat. The onfield call has to be changed. OUT it is and Paine departs. What a review from Rahane. India all over Australia at the moment.
Review time! Indians have taken a caught behind appeal upstairs.
On middle, Paine comes on the front foot and pushes it towards mid off.
Floated on off, driven towards covers this time.
Tossed up and around off, pushed towards mid off.
Full and on middle, clipped through mid-wicket and Paine is off the mark. Single and a wicket from the over.
Landed around off on a length, kept out.
Shortish and on middle, tucked towards the leg side.
Another length ball around off, Paine is solid in defense.
Length ball around off, blocked out.

Skipper Tim Paine is in next. Drinks have been taken though. India right on top here. They smell the victory. They still have got the cushion of 33 runs and will look to run through the remaining 5 wickets as well. A stern challenge for Green and skipper Paine awaits.

OUT! CAUGHT! Siraj strikes on the first ball of his new spell. What an amazing bowling change from Rahane. Half the Aussie side are back in the hut. Siraj is fired up and why not. Australia in all sorts of trouble. A good length ball outside off, Head throws his bat at it as he looks to cut but ends up getting a thick outside edge. It goes straight to Mayank at second slip who takes it easily. Head falls cheaply again.
On middle, played back to the bowler.
Quicker one on the pads, worked on the leg side.
On middle, defends straight back.
On middle and off, punched towards covers.
Flatter around off, fended straight back.
Tossed up around off, defended back.
Flat and just outside off, poked towards point.
Loopy and around off, Head keeps it out off his front foot.
Tossed up and outisde off, Head drives but finds short cover.
On off, driven to mid off for nothing.
Full ball on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Tossed up and around middle, blocked by Head off the front foot.
Who is in next? Will it be Paine? No, Cameron Green it is.

OUT! LBW! Three reds and Wade departs. That looked plumb and Wade knew it but he took the review sensing the importance of this wicket. A quicker one from Jadeja, it is the slider from him. Wade looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get rapped on the pad. The Indians appeal and the finger goes up. Wade is distraught as he knows he is a goner but he takes the review. The technology won't help him as it shows three reds on the Ball Tracker. He has to go. Waste of a review from him. A good, fighting knock from Wade though.

Review time! Wade has been given out LBW! He looks plumb but he goes for the review. Don't think there is any bat Hot Spot and RTS confirms the same. Ball Tracker rolls in and three reds it is. Wade has to go. A review gone too.
Good stop from Ashwin. Short and wide outside off, Wade cuts but Ashwin dives to his left and stops.
Shortish and on middle, worked towards the man at mid-wicket.
Full and around off, pushed towards cover.
Flatter on middle, tucked towards square leg for a single.
On middle, flicked towards fine leg for a couple. Siraj chases the ball and keeps it to two.
On middle, played back to the bowler.
Loopy ball just around off, it turns away as Wade forces it on the off side.
Tossed up and outside off, left alone.
On middle, kept out by Wade.
Loopy around off, Wade is on the front foot to block again.
Tossed up and around off, defended.
Floated on middle and leg, worked towards mid on.
Short and wide outside off, Head looks to cut but misses. Some excitement from the Indians but nothing from the umpire.
Tossed up on middle and leg, turned on the leg side.
On off, blocked off the front foot.
Shortish and around off, turns in as Head punches but finds Ashwin at cover-point who makes a diving stop to his left.
Full and just outside off, poked towards point by Head.
Ripper to end! This one pitches just around off and Wade comes on the front foot to defend but it spins away and whizzes past the outside edge. Pant does well to collect.
Shortish and around off, this time it is punched to the right of the mid off fielder. They take a quick run.
Tossed up on middle, Head blocks again.
Loopy ball around off, a solid front foot defense.
Floated on the pads, Head flicks but finds square leg.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
A single on the last ball as it is worked towards square leg.
Loopy ball on middle, Head works it towards mid-wicket.
Flatter and around off, Head stays back to defend.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed to the left of the bowler.
On off, Wade knocks it on the off side and gets to the other end.
Tossed up outside off, Wade sweeps it wide of the man at fine leg for a couple.
Lovely delivery to end the over. Quicker and just outside off, Head looks to cut but he is cramped for room. Ends up missing it and Pant behind fails to hold on. Was there any bat? No.
On the pads, Head flicks but finds square leg.
Flat and on off, played back to Ashwin by Head.
On middle, flicked to mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed towards the off side.
Flatter and around off, pushed towards point.
Change of ends for Ashwin.
Tossed up and outside off, kept out.
Tossed up and outside off, driven towards mid off.
Flatter and around off, turning in, Head hits it hard on the leg side but Gill comes in the middle and gets a blow on his shoulder.
Short and wide outside off, Head cuts but finds the point fielder.
Tossed up and outside off, Head drives it through the cover region for a couple.
A single on his first ball as Wade pushes it through mid off for one.
Ravindra Jadeja is on now.
Wow! That was a nasty bumper. Head does well to duck as it went past his ear. Sensational stuff.
Length and on the pads, Head flicks it through square leg for a brace.
Back of a length and around off, kept out.
Shortish and around off, Head gets on his toes to defend.
Full and on middle and leg, Head flicks but finds leg gully. It wasn't too far from the fielder.
Good length and around off, Wade tucks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Short and wide, Head cuts but hits the silly point fielder.
Tossed up and around middle, turned on the leg side.
Slower through the air and around middle, worked through mid-wicket for a brace.
Flatter up and around off, Head pushes it towards mid off.
Full and around off, kept out.
Tossed up and outside off, Head lets it be.
Good testing over this by Bumrah. Another Short ball, Wade ducks again.
Short ball again as Wade this time ducks under it.
Time for the concussion test. The physio is out. Wade is looking fine and he is ready to face.
Nasty bumper and Wade gets the blow on his helmet. A bumper and Wade takes his eyes off the ball as he tries to duck away from it. He calls for a new helmet straightaway.
Length ball around off, defended towards the bowler.
Shortish and around off, poked towards point.
Fuller and around middle, Head flicks it towards mid-wicket. Thakur misfields and they run three.
Flatter and around middle and leg, Wade does well to block.
Tossed up this time, Wade stays back to block.
Short and wide outside off, Wade cuts it hard but finds point.
Tossed up and outside off, blocked.
Tossed up and outside off, Wade sweeps it nicely wide of the man at fine leg. Siraj though runs to his right, puts in a dive and stops two.
Fulller and around off, Wade blocks off his front foot.
The extra ball costs two. Shortish and around off, Wade tucks it through square leg for a couple. End of a successful over from Bumrah.
A single to end the successful over for India. Good length and around off, poked towards backward point for one. Bumrah has overstepped. So, he needs to re-bowl this one again.
A bouncer! Wade sits under it.
Length ball around off, Head keeps it out.

Just over! What a welcome for Head! A snortner of a delivery first up. This is just around off, Head hops and tries to fend it off but it takes the gloves and goes over Rahane at gully. A single for Head.
Travis Head comes now to bat at number 5.

OUT! TIMBER! Smith is not sure what happened but the bails are disloged! Smith has been bowled around his legs. He is not sure and is hanging around. A length ball around middle and leg, Smith shuffles across the off side, like he always does and tries to work this one on the leg side but he misses. That doesn't happen often but it has happened here. And the ball goes on to dislodge the bail from the leg and middle pole. Smith is not sure what happened as Bumrah and the Indians celebrate. Smith hangs around and the onfield umpire asks the help from the TV umpire. And one replay is enough. Smith has to go. It is yet another failure for him in this series. A massive, massive moment in the game.
Edgy! Fuller and around off, Smith looks to defend but it goes to gully off the outside edge. Played with soft hands though.

MISFIELD AND FOUR! Tossed up and outside off, Wade throws his bat at the drive and makes a good connection. Agarwal at mid off fails to get to his right and stop the ball cleanly. It races down to the fence at long off.
On off, blocked towards silly point.
Fuller and around off, pushed to mid off.
Tosses this up but Wade is happy to defend again.
Slower through the air and around off, blocked from the crease.
