Good length and around off, it is angled in. Smith flicks but square leg dives to his right to stop.
Fuller and around off, blocked towards mid on by Smith.
Good length and just around off, pushed on the off side.
Shortish and around off, blocked off the back foot.
Another solid defense to end the over.
Tossed up and around middle, Wade is on the front foot to block.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle and leg, kept out.

What happened there? A tossed up ball just around off, it pitches and bounces over the stumps to beat the bat. Pant is beaten too. The ball lobs off the shoulder of Pant and goes behind. Rahane goes back to field.
And Smith nudges one towards mid-wicket to get to the other end.
Will it be Ashwin from the other end? With Smith on strike, surely! Yes, here he is. 10-2-24-1 are his numbers so far.
Very full and on middle, flicked towards mid on for nothing.
Length ball around off and middle, pushed to mid on.
Pitches this up and bowls it just around off, Wade defends it out.
Another one just outside off, Wade covers his stumps and lets it go to Pant.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Run straightaway for Smith! A length ball around off, Smith pushes it towards mid on and calls for a run.

Time for the final session of the moving day of the Test match. India still with an advantage as their players take the field. Matthew Wade and Steven Smith follow them out in the middle as well. Jasprit Bumrah to start after Tea.
... Day 3, Final Session ...

The Indians were right on the money as Umesh struck early to dismiss Burns for another low score. Umesh though left the field after having issues with his calf and after that Wade along with Labuschagne controlled things nicely and added 38 between them. Most of the runs came off the bat of Marnus who looked more positive than Wade. But as the stand between the two was growing, Ashwin struck and got the better of Labuschagne. Smith and Wade after that managed to see off the remaining session. The task for them will get bigger when they come out to bat in the final session of the day. India would look to get the big fish Smith and then they can maybe breathe a bit easy. The final session coming your way shortly.

That was some brilliant stuff from Ashwin and Wade in the final over! Good from Pant as well as he kept talking throughout the over and put pressure on Wade! Test cricket at its absolute best! The session one would feel has gone to both the teams.
Another one tossed up outside off, Wade covers his stumps and allows it to go to the keeper. With that, it is TEA ON DAY 3.
Tosses it up full and wide, turns away, Wade lets it be.

Was there some bat? Maybe not. Lovely from Ashwin. Flatter and around the pads, Wade goes back and looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball lobs towards forward short leg. The fielder lunges forward to take the catch but it drops short. Wasn't any bat anyway.
Tossed up and around off, Wade keeps it out.
Tossed up and outside off, Wade is early in his defense as he ends up hitting it uppishly wide of the cover fielder.
Smith takes a single on the first ball. Full and around middle, Smith pushes it to wide of the man at mid on for a run.
We will get another over!
Bumper on middle, Wade sits again.
In the channel outside off, left alone this time.
FOUR! Lovely drive! A fuller ball on the stumps, Wade drives this past mid on to get a boundary here.
Three in a row! Bumrah wants to keep Wade on strike! India want another one from Ashwin to to Smith.
Another short one. Easily evaded by Wade.
Bumper down the leg side. Wade ducks.

Nearly a wicket! Superb over from Ashwin. He set Smith up nicely. He got him out similarly in the first innings. And, almost got him here. Pitches it around off and middle and then it turns in with some extra bounce. Smith looks to work it on the leg side but gets it off the inside edge. It though doesn't carry to Pujara this time.
Tossed up and just outside off, Smith stays back to block.
Tossed up and outside off, Smith goes for the slog sweep. Doesn't connect it well and it goes to square leg.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
On middle, Smith comes forward and bunts it on the leg side.
Flatter and around off, pushed toards mid on.
Shortish around off, punched straight to the fielder at covers.
Length ball around off, Wade defends it back to the bowler.
Short ball on middle and leg, Wade comfortably ducks under it.
Shortish around middle, Wade blocks this towards mid on.
Fuller ball on middle, Wade drives this down the ground and they take a couple before Siraj who chases the ball from mid off returns the ball back.
Length ball around middle, worked towards mid-wicket.
Jasprit Bumrah is back. 6-1-14-0 are his numbers so far.
Quicker one around off, turned on the leg side.
Quick single as Wade drives it wide of the man at mid off.
Shortish and just outside off, punched towards cover.
Shortish and outside off, punched towards cover for one.
Floated around off, defended straight by Smith.
Tossed up around off, Smith comes down the track but gets an inside edge on his pads.
Fuller ball around off, driven towards mid off.
Length ball angling across, left alone by Wade.
Length ball around off, Wade defends it towards point.
Outside off, going further away. Wade lets it be.
Length ball around off, blocked off the front foot.
Full and around off, Smith uses his wrists and flicks it between square leg and leg gully for three. Nice work.
On middle, Wade keeps it out.
Another one wide outside off, Wade leaves it alone.
Tossed up outside off, Wade lets it be.
Tossed up and around off, blocked off the front foot.
Tossed up outside off, Wade brings the sweep shot and hits it towards fine leg for one
Tossed up on the stumps, defended straight back.
Length ball around off, Smith blocks this out.
Fuller ball around off, angling in, Smith nudges it towards leg gully.
Short of a length outside off, punched nicely towards deep point for a single.
Similar ball outside off, Wade leaves it alone.
Length ball around off, left alone.
50 up for Australia as they run 4. A fullish length on middle, Wade flicks this at the gap through mid-wicket and runs four as Gill does well to chase it down.

Appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire and nothing either from the bowler. A tossed up ball on middle and leg, Wade goes for the sweep but gets it off the inside edge towards short fine leg. They take a run.
On the pads, Smith flicks it to deep mid-wicket and opens his account.
Flatter and around off, Smith stays back to block this time.
Flat and around off, Smith comes on the front foot to block.
On middle, kept out.
Tossed up and just outside off, turns in, Smith defends.
Shortish around middle, Wade punches this one wide of mid-wicket and takes a couple.
Length around middle, Wade taps this one on the off side.
Fuller ball on middle, flicked straight to mid-wicket.
Shortish outside off, poked towards point.
Length ball around middle, defended by Wade.

NOT OUT! Pitching outside leg. A poor review from India this time. A length ball pitched down the leg side. It angles across the left-hander. Wade fails to put bat on ball and is hit on the pad. They appeal but not out says the umpire. That looked to pitching outside leg but Siraj is absolutely sure that he has got his man. Rahane goes with the bowler. And well, replays show it to be a poor call as it has pitched way outside leg. Poor, poor review.

Another review from India. This is against Wade for LBW. Once again Siraj is absolutely certain and Rahane goes with the bowler. Time for the replays! Noting on Hot Spot and nothing either on RTS. Ball Tracker again. It is pitching outside leg. This time India lose a review.
Tossed up and on middle, tucked towards mid-wicket. End of a successful over from Ashwin.
Steven Smith now in at number 4. Interesting battle to look forward to.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ashwin strikes and provides the much-needed breakthrough to the Indians. Lovely loopy ball around off and middle from him this time. It pitches and then turns in to Marnus. Labuschagne looks to defend coming forward but it takes the outside edge and goes straight to Rahane at first slip. The Indian skipper takes the catch easily. Good, little innings from him but Australia needed him to carry on.
Flat and around off, blocked by Marnus.
Tossed up and around off, kept out.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter and on middle, tucked on the leg side for nothing.
Just outside off on a length, poked towards Rahane at gully.
FOUR! This should settle the nerves for Wade. Short and wide outside off, Wade crunches it through backward of point and finds the fence.
Full and outside off, a mistimed drive towards cover this time.
Shortish and just outside off, Wade looks to punch but mistimes it.
Fuller and around off, kept out.
Good length and around off, pushed towards point.
Tossed up around middle, nudged towards short fine leg.
Fuller ball on middle, tucks it on the leg side.
Tossed up around leg, tucks it towards leg gully.
Flatter around middle, swept towards fine leg for a single.
Fuller around off, defended straight towards the cover fielder.
Loopy ball around off, driven through the covers and they take three before the fielder returns it back.
Fuller ball on the stumps, Wade blocks this out.
Shortish around off, Wade pushes it towards point and runs but is sent back by his partner. A risk is involved when the fielder ther is Jadeja.
Short ball outside off, Marnus pulls this uppishly but just falls wide of the square leg fielder and they take a single. Labuschagne is living dangerously here.

Review time! Rahane wasn't too sure but he went with his bowler. Time for Hot Spot first. No bat on it and nothing on the RTS either. Time for Ball Tracker. Pitching in line, impact in line but umpire's call on hitting the wickets.

NOT OUT! Umpire's call on hitting the wickets, AGAIN! Luck with Labuschagne here. A length ball that is pitched outside off, it comes back in sharply and hits the pad as he fails to connect. It looked to be hitting him high on the pads but Rahane takes the review. Replays show everything is perfect but it is just clipping the stumps. So, Marnus survives. A good review from India though as it could've gone either way.
Fuller this time around off, Marnus drives it towards imd off.
Length around middle, flicked straight to square leg.
Tossed up and outside off, Wade pushes it towards point.
On off, Wade keeps it out.
Short and wide outside off, punched through covers. Three taken before the fielder can chase it down.
Loopy ball around off, blocked.
Full and on middle and leg, Labuschagne looks to defend but gets an inside edge that goes past the keeper towards fine leg. They take two.
Tossed up and around middle, worked towards short fine leg.

DRINKS! Australia have done well in spite of losing a wicket in this hour! Indians have not bowled badly but they have given away easy singles and that has not helped them one bit. Umesh's absence in the middle will hurt them more. Let's see how the Indian bowlers return post this mini-break.
Length ball angling across, Wade lets it be.
A fuller length outside off angling across, left alone by Wade.
Short of a length around middle, turned away towards fine leg for a single.
Fuller around middle, Marnus flicks it towards square leg but can't beat him.
A fuller length ball around off, Marnus plays it on the leg side.
Length ball around off, blocked solidly.
Mohamed Siraj is back on.
Full and on middle and leg, Wade negotiates it easily.
On middle, blocked out by Wade.
Three now! Short and wide outside off, Labuschagne cuts it to the left of Siraj who gives it a chase. A single saved near the ropes.
Slightly short around off, driven to the left of covers and they take a run. Siraj though midfields at covers and concedes another one.
Tossed up around off nudges towards square leg.
Fullish around off, driven straight to covers.
Single to end as the last ball is flicked down to deep mid-wicket for one.
Length and around off, pushed towards mid on.
Back of a length and around off, kept out.
In the channel outside off, a leave from Labuschagne.
Shortish and just outside off, poked towards the gully fielder.
Length ball around off, watchfully defended by Labuschagne.
Fuller and on the pads, nudged towards short fine leg.
Tossed up and around off, Wade blocks it out.
Another loopy ball around off, kept out.
Tosses this one to the left-hander now and Wade defends it off the front foot.
A single now as this quicker one is nudged down to deep square leg. This one pitched around off and spun back in.
Lovely drive to welcome Ashwin from Labuschagne. Ashwin tosses it full and bowls it wide outside off, it is driven through covers for a brace.
Spin time! Umesh Yadav is off the field and Rahane tosses the ball to Ashwin. He was the one who sent Wade packing. Can he do that again?
Shortish this time around middle, Wade blocks this out on the off side.
Fuller length around off, played towards mid-wicket.
A fuller length on middle, Wade defends it straight back.
Length around middle, flicked towards square leg for a run.
A length ball outside off, Marnus leaves it alone.
FOUR! Nicely driven down the ground by Labuschagne as it was fuller ball around off. The mid on fielder had no chance to stop that one.
Length outside off, Wade plays it towards point.
Good length around off, dabbed it towards point.
Siraj starts with a fuller ball outside off, Wade lets it go.

Bumper around middle and leg, Wade ducks under it. Umesh is limping and he is looking in some pain here. Yes. He is going off. Not a great sign for the Indians. Let's hope there is nothing serious. The Indians will surely want that because he was looking really good.Siraj will continue the over.
Shortish around middle, Wade blocks this out.
On a length outside off, left alone by Wade.
Around off on a length, defended off the front foot.
Third single in the over. A fuller one outside off, Wade pushes it towards cover and goes for a run as Siraj fumbles.
Angled in from around off, Labuschagne tucks it wide of the fine leg fielder for one.
Fuller and around off, worked towards square leg.
A bumper but it goes well over Labuschagne.
Another quick single. Fuller and around off, Wade pushes it gently towards cover for a quick run.
Close! A good leave though. This is good from Umesh too. He continies to bowl it just around off on a length. Marnus though is covering his sticks as he shoulders arms.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Leading edge! A fullish ball around middle and leg, it pitches and then straightens a touch. Labuschagne looks to flick but gets a leading edge. Rahane at gully dives to his right to make a stop.
Now Wade pokes one towards the off side for a quick single. Good from Australia.
Another quick run! Full and around off, Labuschagne pushes it towards cover and takes a run.
Good leave! But this wasn't too far away from the off pole. A shortish and outside off, comes back in a touch as Labuschagne lets it be. Goes just past the off pole but it was over it.
A leave to end! This one is angled in from outside off but Wade is sure about his off pole as he shoulders arms.
Banged in on middle, goes well over Wade who ducks. Good from Pant behind the sticks.
Fuller and around off, Labuschagne taps it on the off side and gets to the other end.
Fuller and around off, pushed to mid on.
Good length and around off Labuschagne defends it out.
Length around off, pushes it towards covers and takes a run.
Shortish around off, pushes it on the off side and takes a quick run. A successful over from Yadav.
Shortish around off, dabs it on the off side.
Good length around off, Wade blocks it out.
Length ball around middle, defended towards mid-wicket.
Fuller ball sliding down, Marnus flicks this one towards fine leg for a single and gets off the mark.
Who will come next? Marnus Labuschagne it is at number 3.
Burns has been given out caught behind now. He has taken the review with moments left on the timer. The Hot Spot detects the edge. Burns goes and takes the review along with him.

OUT! CAUGHT! This time Burns has to go. A superb delivery from Yadav. This one pitches just around off and then goes away just a hint. Burns has to play at it. And he does that but only ends up getting a nick behind. Pant makes no mistake and the Indians celebrate. However, Burns gets to his partner at the other end and decides to challenge the onfield call, at the very last moment. Time for the replays. And only one is all we need. The Hot Spot detects a faint outside edge. Another failure for Burns and this time he takes a review along with him. Poor from the Aussie opener. An unplayable ball from Umesh though that would've got best of the batsmen out.
A fuller length around off, defended towards point.
NIce drive! A fuller ball outside off, Burns drives this one through the covers and take three before the fielder returns the ball back.
A length ball outside off, pushed towards point.
Fuller length just outside off, Burns shoulders arms to it.
Good length in the channel outside off, left alone by Burns.

NOT OUT! Burns survives. The umpire's call saves Burns here. A terrific delivery from Bumrah. He runs in and bowls a perfect yorker. Burns looks to flick but he falls over as he tries to play across the line. He misses and the Indians appeal but the umpire turns it down. Rahane goes for the review after having a word with the bowler and other close-in fielders. Replays show that it has hit the shoes. But Ball Tracker confirms it to be umpire's call on hitting the wickets. A good review from India.
Review time! Where's that hit him? It has hit the shoes. Ball Tracker time! Pitching in line, impact is in line as well but wickets umpire's call. Burns stays. India keep their review.
Back of a length and around middle, Wade is on his toes to block. 1 from Umesh's first.
Length ball around off, pushed towards point.

Quick single and Burns is off the pair. A direct hit though would've been close. Fuller and around middle, Burns works it towards mid-wicket and goes for a run. Ashwin has a shy at the non-striker's end but he misses as Burns dives to make his crease.
Good leave! This one pitches around off and moves a touch as Burns shoulders arms. It goes just over the stumps.

Right! We are back for the second session! The Indian players are in a huddle near the rope. They now disperse to take their positions in the field. Joe Burns and Matthew Wade stride out to open the Aussie innings. In the first innings, Burns fell for a duck while Wade looked decent for his knock. They will have to play a big role if the Aussies are to get to a good score. Jasprit Bumrah will take the new ball for India. He was the one who gave the first wicket to the Indians. Rahane will want it from him again. Three men catching at slips, one at gully. Here we go...
Full but down the leg side, Burns looks to flick but misses.
Length ball around off, kept out.
Who will take the ball from the other end? Umesh Yadav it is. Didn't get a wicket in the first innings. Let's see what he can do here. Burns to face.
A maiden to start from Bumrah. This one is around off on a length, Wade comes on the front foot to defend. Top first over from Bumrah.
In the channel outside off, Wade offers no shot to it.
Fuller and around off, it comes back in, Wade does well to keep it out.
Wide outside off, left alone again by Wade.
A length ball, this one is pitched around off, it keeps going away as Wade lets it be.

Appeal straightaway! A loud one from India but not out says the umpire. A length ball around the pads, Wade looks to work it out on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pad. They all go up in appeal but nothing from the umpire. No review from India and a good call because replay shows it was pitched outside leg.

That's all from this game. This marks the end of 2020 for both these teams. 2021 brings a lot of excitement as the two teams meet on 7th January 2021 for the 3rd Test of the series. The game is scheduled to take place in Sydney. However, there are chances that it can happen at the MCG itself due to Covid-19 issues. Anyway, the action will begin at 1030 local (2330 GMT PREVIOUS DAY). Do join us for that game. For now, goodbye and take care.

Australia skipper, Tim Paine, says that they are really disappointed. Feels that they played poor cricket for the majority of the game. Says they were sloppy and if you give a bit to a good side like India, it is always difficult. Credits the Indian bowling attack and says they failed to adapt against them. Adds that there are a couple of games left in this series so they will try to rectify that. On Green, Paine says that he has started really well in his career. Tells that they will stay together in the next few days before the third Test.

Ajinkya Rahane, the Indian skipper is named Player of the Match! He starts by saying that he is really proud of the boys. Praises Gill and Siraj for showing character, after their last game at Adelaide. Mentions it was sad to miss out on Yadav. Tells that their plan to go with 5 bowlers worked really well. Adds with Jadeja batting well, it helped them really well. On Gill, Rahane says that Gill has a great first-class record. Says he showed great character. On Siraj, Rahane feels his first-class experience helped him here. On him captaining the side, Rahane says that the talk was about showing attitude and character going into this game. Tells that the Aussies batted really well in the second innings and they had to work hard for their wickets. On Yadav's injury, Rahane says that he is recovering well. On Rohit's availability, Rahane says that they are excited to have him and he spoke to Rohit who also is eager to get back in the side.
Stay tuned for the presentation!

Right! 1-1 now! When India lost the first game the world knew Kohli is not going to feature for the rest of the series, not many gave this Indian team a chance, provided after their humiliating defeat in the first Test. But India have put that thought to rest to bag an impressive win and set up the series brilliantly.

It was all about the Indian bowlers after that as they demolished the Aussie batting. The Aussies lost 6 with the score not even crossing 100 and it looked like the game might well get over on Day 3 itself but the stubborn stand between Cummins and Green forced the game to Day 4. You already know what happened on Day 4. A clinical performance from Rahane's men to level the series.

In response, skipper Rahane led the charge in the absence of Kohli and brought up a fine ton. He along with Vihari and Pant added valuable runs and kept the score moving. However, his 121-run stand along with Jadeja gave the Indians a very good lead. They had the chance of swelling that lead more after the wicket of Rahane in the first session on Day 3, the Indians collapsed. Starc and Lyon got 3 apiece with the ball for the Aussies.

Earlier in the game, after winning the toss, Australia opted to bat first but the decision turned out to be a disastrous one as they lost 3 wickets quickly. Labuschagne and Head added 86 runs between them to give the Aussies some control but once Head was removed. the Aussies collapsed big time and got rolled over to just 195. It was Bumrah who was the chief tormentor with the ball as he picked up 4. Ashwin got 3 while the debutant Siraj bagged a couple of wickets as well.

When Day 4 began, it was always about how long the remaining Aussie 4 batters could battle. They did battle, an entire session which was extended by 30 minutes after India got the 9th wicket and eventually, in the last over of the extended session, Ashwin got rid of the last man. Needing 70, India once again lost Agarwal early but Gill showed his class in this little knock. Pujara fell too but the skipper who got a ton in the last innings, played a few fine shots to take the team home.

What a moment for India. They have created history here. Their back-to-back Test wins at the MCG! Don't forget the kind of humiliation they went through in the first Test. And then bouncing back and doing what they have done, that too without their charismatic leader and batsman Virat Kohli, is a commendable job by Rahane's men. He must be a proud leader. Take a bow!
Rahane finds the winning run this time. A short ball on middle, Rahane pulls it towards square leg where the fielder fumbles and they take one. India win by 8 wickets.
Short and on middle, Rahane finds mid-wicket again.
Three dots! Flatter and around middle, Rahane comes down the track and tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Shortish and around middle, Rahane works it towards mid-wicket. He thinks for a single but returns back.
Tossed up and around off, blocked.

Good stop near the ropes! But scores are level. Full and outside, Rahane drives it through the covers. The ball is racing towards the fence in the deep. This might well be the winning runs but no. Cummins from covers gives it a chase and stops it with a dive, allowing the batsmen to take three more.
On middle, blocked out.
Short and down the leg side, pulled but straight to short fine leg.
Short and wide outside off, punched for a run to cover-point.
FOUR! Whipped! 7th boundary for Gill already. Fuller and on the pads, Gill uses his wrists and whips it past the man at mid on. It races away to the fence.
A short ball from him, Rahane pulls it down to deep square leg for one.
Marnus Labuschagne to bowl.
Tossed up and around off, Gill comes on the front foot and bunts.
Flat and on middle, this one is nudged through square leg for a run.
Shortish and around off, worked on the off side.
Tossed up and around off, kept out.

Dropped! Good effort from Starc though. Lyon tosses it up and Rahane comes down the track. He flicks it to the right side of the man at long on. Starc runs that side, dives and gets both hands but fails to hold on.
Flatter and around off, pushed back to Lyon.
Fuller and around off, Gill offers straight bat to block.
FOUR! Take that! Josh runs in and bowls a short ball on middle, Gill swivels and pulls it powerfully through mid-wicket. No chance for the man at deep square leg to get to it.
Length ball around off, Gill pushes it to mid on.
This time he is right behind the line of the ball to defend.
No run, Beaten! Good length and outside off, Gill pokes at it to get beaten.
Good length and around off, worked towards mid on by Gill.
Tossed up and around off, Rahane keeps it out.
Tossed up and turning in, Gill tucks it towards fine leg for a run.
Loopy ball around off, pushed back to the bowler.
On off, kept out.
Floated on off, played back to Lyon.
Tossed up and around off, Gill comes on the front foot to block.
Time for spin! Nathan Lyon is on.
FOUR! SHOT! Super shot from Rahane! 50 is up for India. A fullish ball outside off, Rahane drills it through the covers for a boundary.
Full and around off, stroked to mid on for nothing.
Play and a miss! Good length and outside off, Rahane goes for the drive away from his body to miss out.
Fuller and around off, a solid front foot block.
A bumper now and Rahane pulls it. It is wide of the fine leg fielder and Rahane gets a couple.
FOUR! Width offered and Rahane pounces on it. Short and wide outside off, Rahane goes back and punches it on the up. It goes right in the gap between point and gully for a boundary.
Full and outside off, a solid drive but Cummins stops.
A bumper! Gill ducks under it.
FOUR! Another boundary for Gill. Full and wide outside off, he leans into the stroke and drills it through cover-point for a boundary. Brilliant batting.
Good length and around off, blocked.
Quick run! Length ball around off, Rahane tucks it towards mid-wicket and calls for one.
Shortish and on the body, tucked to fine leg for one by Gill.
Good length and around off, solidly defended.
Around off on a good length, defended off the front foot.
Good length and around off, solidly defended.
Josh Hazlewood to Ajinkya Rahane, Around off, kept out.
Good length and around off, Rahane blocks again.
Josh Hazlewood to Ajinkya Rahane, Good length and around off, solidly defended.
Josh Hazlewood is on!

Shot! Full and outside off, Rahane leans into the shot and strokes it through the covers. The fielder from the ring gives it a chase but by the time the ball is returned, they take three. India have got to the score where they had lost 9 in the last game.
Fuller and just outside off, Rahane drives it towards the man at point.
Shortish and just outside off, pushed towards point.
Good length and around off, kept out.

Huge appeal but turned down. A length ball angled in, Rahane looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. They all go up in appeal but not out says the umpire. Cummins suggests that there was some bat.
Good length and outside off, poked to the left of the point fielder who dives to his left and stops.
Shortish and around middle, worked towards square leg for one.
A bumper now and Gill pulls it down to deep square leg for one.
FOUR! Soft hands! Good length and outside off, Gill waits and then just guides it with soft hands. It goes right in between gully and slip cordon.
Shortish and outside off, poked towards point.
FOUR! Gill with another fine shot. He continues to impress here. A short ball just outside off, Gill stays back and slashes it through point for a boundary.
Fuller and outside off, it is left alone.
Back of a length and around off, poked towards point for nothing. Successful over from Cummins.
Looks to pull again but is beaten for pace, is Rahane. He gets hit on the body.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
FOUR! What a way to open your account. Cummins bangs it short and on middle, Rahane swivels and nails the pull over backward square leg for a boundary.
Length ball around off, kept out.
Who will come out to bat now? Skipper Ajinkya Rahane it is. He would like to continue from where he left in the 1st innings.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another one bites the dust! Pujara is the man and he falls to Cummins. Is there a twist in this game? A fuller ball outside off, shapes away a touch. Pujara looks to drive but gets an outside edge. The ball goes to gully uppishly. Green there takes the chance easily.
Short and wide outside off, punched to the man at point. End of a successful over from Starc.
Taps the next fuller one towards point and gets to the other end.
Fuller and around off, pushed to mid off.
Pujars is up and running with a brace. Starc targets the stumps and bowls it full on middle, Pujara flicks and bags two.
Cheteshwar Pujara is in at number 3 now.

OUT! TAKEN! Starc gets one. Poor from Agarwal. He fails in this short run chase. Hasn't been a great tour for him and it continues to be that way. It is just outside off on a length, it pitches and moves away. Agarwal looks to drive it on the up and ends up getting a nick behind. Paine accepts the chance easily.
Nicley pulled! A well-directed bumper but Gill does really well to play a controlled pull shot wide of the man at fine leg. A single.
Around off on a length, Agarwal lets the ball to come close and then forces it towards gully.
Full and outside off, Mayank leans into the drive and strokes it through covers for a brace.
Outside off again, Agarwal lets it be.
Good length and just outside off, poked towards point off the front foot. Good, positive stride from him.
Another leave as Cummins continues to bowl in the channel on a good length.
In the channel outside off, Agarwal shoulders arms.
Shortish and around off, Gill gets on top of the bounce and taps it on the off side.
This time the line is way wide outside off, Gill shoulders arms.
Beaten! Flirts with one which is outside off to get beaten.
Good length and around off, watchfully blocked off the back foot.
FOUR! WOW! What a shot! Gill bags another boundary. Starc overpitches it around off, Gill meets it with straight bat and just punches the drive through mid off. It races away to the fence.
Fuller and around off, pushed to mid off
Works the last ball through backward square leg for a couple of runs.
Another ripper! Sensational from Cummins. This one pitches just outside off and comes back in again as Agarwal pokes. Only to get beaten.
Nicely bowled! Pitches this one outside off and it comes back in sharply. Agarwal is caught on crease as he tries to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Length ball around middle, tucked on the leg side.
Taps the next one towards point and takes a run.

FOUR! SHOT! Full and wide outside off, Gill strokes it through the covers for a boundary. Super shot from Gill. Tells you how confident this young man is. Classy shot against the no. 1 Test bowler in the world.
Who will bowl from the other end? Pat Cummins it is.
Gill is off the mark on the last ball of the over. A length ball around middle, Gill works it down to deep square leg to open his account.
Chance but a tough one. A length ball around middle, Gill flicks. There is a forward short leg. Wade it is. The ball goes straight to him but he fails to hold on.
Agarwal is up and running. A length ball around middle and leg, Agarwal tucks it towards deep square leg for one.
Play and a miss! Lovely ball from Starc. He makes this one to come back in from around off and cut Mayank in half.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards the off side.
Starc is on the money straightaway. A shortish length ball around off, angles in as Agarwal fails to put bat on ball and is hit on high on the pad.

Right! We are back. 70 is the target. Mayank Agarwal and Shubhman Gill stride out to the middle to open the innings. The Aussie players are out in the middle already. Mitchell Starc to take the new ball.
